63#ifndef CATCH_COMPILER_CAPABILITIES_HPP_INCLUDED

66// Detect a number of compiler features - by compiler
67// The following features are defined:
68//
69// CATCH_CONFIG_WINDOWS_SEH : is Windows SEH supported?
70// CATCH_CONFIG_POSIX_SIGNALS : are POSIX signals supported?
71// CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS : Are exceptions enabled?
72// ****************
73// Note to maintainers: if new toggles are added please document them
74// in configuration.md, too
75// ****************
76
77// In general each macro has a _NO_<feature name> form
78// (e.g. CATCH_CONFIG_NO_POSIX_SIGNALS) which disables the feature.
79// Many features, at point of detection, define an _INTERNAL_ macro, so they
80// can be combined, en-mass, with the _NO_ forms later.
81
82

92# endif

112# endif

114#elif defined(__ORBIS__) || defined(__PROSPERO__)
115# define CATCH_PLATFORM_PLAYSTATION

117#endif

219// As of this writing, IBM XL's implementation of __builtin_constant_p has a bug
220// which results in calls to destructors being emitted for each temporary,
221// without a matching initialization. In practice, this can result in something
222// like `std::string::~string` being called on an uninitialized value.
223//
224// For example, this code will likely segfault under IBM XL:
225// ```
226// REQUIRE(std::string("12") + "34" == "1234")
227// ```
228//
229// Similarly, NVHPC's implementation of `__builtin_constant_p` has a bug which
230// results in calls to the immediately evaluated lambda expressions to be
231// reported as unevaluated lambdas.
232// https://developer.nvidia.com/nvidia_bug/3321845.
233//
234// Therefore, `CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN` is not implemented.
235#if defined( __ibmxl__ ) || defined( __CUDACC__ ) || defined( __NVCOMPILER )
236# define CATCH_INTERNAL_CONFIG_NO_USE_BUILTIN_CONSTANT_P
237#endif

477 (void)__builtin_constant_p( __VA_ARGS__ ) /* NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg, \

565namespace Catch {
566
567 class IResultCapture;
568 class IConfig;
569
570 class Context {
571 IConfig const* m_config = nullptr;
572 IResultCapture* m_resultCapture = nullptr;
573
574 CATCH_EXPORT static Context currentContext;
575 friend Context& getCurrentMutableContext();
576 friend Context const& getCurrentContext();
577
578 public:
579 constexpr IResultCapture* getResultCapture() const {
580 return m_resultCapture;
581 }
582 constexpr IConfig const* getConfig() const { return m_config; }
583 constexpr void setResultCapture( IResultCapture* resultCapture ) {
584 m_resultCapture = resultCapture;
585 }
586 constexpr void setConfig( IConfig const* config ) { m_config = config; }
587 };
588
589 Context& getCurrentMutableContext();
590
591 inline Context const& getCurrentContext() {
592 return Context::currentContext;
593 }

694#ifndef CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED
695#define CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED
696
697#include <cstddef>
698#include <string>
699#include <iosfwd>
700#include <cassert>
701
702#include <cstring>
703
704namespace Catch {
705
709 class StringRef {
710 public:
711 using size_type = std::size_t;
712 using const_iterator = const char*;
713
714 static constexpr size_type npos{ static_cast<size_type>( -1 ) };
715
716 private:
717 static constexpr char const* const s_empty = "";
718
719 char const* m_start = s_empty;
720 size_type m_size = 0;
721
722 public: // construction
723 constexpr StringRef() noexcept = default;
724
725 StringRef( char const* rawChars ) noexcept;
726
727 constexpr StringRef( char const* rawChars, size_type size ) noexcept
728 : m_start( rawChars ),
729 m_size( size )
730 {}
731
732 StringRef( std::string const& stdString ) noexcept
733 : m_start( stdString.c_str() ),
734 m_size( stdString.size() )
735 {}
736
737 explicit operator std::string() const {
738 return std::string(m_start, m_size);
739 }
740
741 public: // operators
742 auto operator == ( StringRef other ) const noexcept -> bool {
743 return m_size == other.m_size
744 && (std::memcmp( m_start, other.m_start, m_size ) == 0);
745 }
746 auto operator != (StringRef other) const noexcept -> bool {
747 return !(*this == other);
748 }
749
750 constexpr auto operator[] ( size_type index ) const noexcept -> char {
751 assert(index < m_size);
752 return m_start[index];
753 }
754
755 bool operator<(StringRef rhs) const noexcept;
756
757 public: // named queries
758 constexpr auto empty() const noexcept -> bool {
759 return m_size == 0;
760 }
761 constexpr auto size() const noexcept -> size_type {
762 return m_size;
763 }
764
765 // Returns a substring of [start, start + length).
766 // If start + length > size(), then the substring is [start, size()).
767 // If start > size(), then the substring is empty.
768 constexpr StringRef substr(size_type start, size_type length) const noexcept {
769 if (start < m_size) {
770 const auto shortened_size = m_size - start;
771 return StringRef(m_start + start, (shortened_size < length) ? shortened_size : length);
772 } else {
773 return StringRef();
774 }
775 }
776
777 // Returns the current start pointer. May not be null-terminated.
778 constexpr char const* data() const noexcept {
779 return m_start;
780 }
781
782 constexpr const_iterator begin() const { return m_start; }
783 constexpr const_iterator end() const { return m_start + m_size; }
784
785
786 friend std::string& operator += (std::string& lhs, StringRef rhs);
787 friend std::ostream& operator << (std::ostream& os, StringRef str);
788 friend std::string operator+(StringRef lhs, StringRef rhs);
789
796 int compare( StringRef rhs ) const;
797 };
798
799
800 constexpr auto operator ""_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> StringRef {
801 return StringRef( rawChars, size );
802 }
803} // namespace Catch
804
805constexpr auto operator ""_catch_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> Catch::StringRef {
806 return Catch::StringRef( rawChars, size );
807}
808
809#endif // CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED

812#ifndef CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
813#define CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
814
815namespace Catch {
816
817 // ResultWas::OfType enum
818 struct ResultWas { enum OfType {
819 Unknown = -1,
820 Ok = 0,
821 Info = 1,
822 Warning = 2,
823 // TODO: Should explicit skip be considered "not OK" (cf. isOk)? I.e., should it have the failure bit?
824 ExplicitSkip = 4,
825
826 FailureBit = 0x10,
827
828 ExpressionFailed = FailureBit | 1,
829 ExplicitFailure = FailureBit | 2,
830
831 Exception = 0x100 | FailureBit,
832
833 ThrewException = Exception | 1,
834 DidntThrowException = Exception | 2,
835
836 FatalErrorCondition = 0x200 | FailureBit
837
838 }; };
839
840 constexpr bool isOk( ResultWas::OfType resultType ) {
841 return ( resultType & ResultWas::FailureBit ) == 0;
842 }
843 constexpr bool isJustInfo( int flags ) { return flags == ResultWas::Info; }
844
845
846 // ResultDisposition::Flags enum
847 struct ResultDisposition { enum Flags {
848 Normal = 0x01,
849
850 ContinueOnFailure = 0x02, // Failures fail test, but execution continues
851 FalseTest = 0x04, // Prefix expression with !
852 SuppressFail = 0x08 // Failures are reported but do not fail the test
853 }; };
854
855 constexpr ResultDisposition::Flags operator|( ResultDisposition::Flags lhs,
856 ResultDisposition::Flags rhs ) {
857 return static_cast<ResultDisposition::Flags>( static_cast<int>( lhs ) |
858 static_cast<int>( rhs ) );
859 }
860
861 constexpr bool isFalseTest( int flags ) {
862 return ( flags & ResultDisposition::FalseTest ) != 0;
863 }
864 constexpr bool shouldSuppressFailure( int flags ) {
865 return ( flags & ResultDisposition::SuppressFail ) != 0;
866 }
867
868} // end namespace Catch
869
870#endif // CATCH_RESULT_TYPE_HPP_INCLUDED
871
872
873#ifndef CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
874#define CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
875
876#include <cassert>
877#include <type_traits>
878
879
880namespace Catch {
881namespace Detail {
887 template <typename T>
888 class unique_ptr {
889 T* m_ptr;
890 public:
891 constexpr unique_ptr(std::nullptr_t = nullptr):
892 m_ptr{}
893 {}
894 explicit constexpr unique_ptr(T* ptr):
895 m_ptr(ptr)
896 {}
897
898 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
899 unique_ptr(unique_ptr<U>&& from):
900 m_ptr(from.release())
901 {}
902
903 template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
904 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr<U>&& from) {
905 reset(from.release());
906
907 return *this;
908 }
909
910 unique_ptr(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
911 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
912
913 unique_ptr(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept:
914 m_ptr(rhs.m_ptr) {
915 rhs.m_ptr = nullptr;
916 }
917 unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept {
918 reset(rhs.release());
919
920 return *this;
921 }
922
923 ~unique_ptr() {
924 delete m_ptr;
925 }
926
927 T& operator*() {
928 assert(m_ptr);
929 return *m_ptr;
930 }
931 T const& operator*() const {
932 assert(m_ptr);
933 return *m_ptr;
934 }
935 T* operator->() noexcept {
936 assert(m_ptr);
937 return m_ptr;
938 }
939 T const* operator->() const noexcept {
940 assert(m_ptr);
941 return m_ptr;
942 }
943
944 T* get() { return m_ptr; }
945 T const* get() const { return m_ptr; }
946
947 void reset(T* ptr = nullptr) {
948 delete m_ptr;
949 m_ptr = ptr;
950 }
951
952 T* release() {
953 auto temp = m_ptr;
954 m_ptr = nullptr;
955 return temp;
956 }
957
958 explicit operator bool() const {
959 return m_ptr != nullptr;
960 }
961
962 friend void swap(unique_ptr& lhs, unique_ptr& rhs) {
963 auto temp = lhs.m_ptr;
964 lhs.m_ptr = rhs.m_ptr;
965 rhs.m_ptr = temp;
966 }
967 };
968
970 template <typename T>
971 class unique_ptr<T[]>;
972
973 template <typename T, typename... Args>
974 unique_ptr<T> make_unique(Args&&... args) {
975 return unique_ptr<T>(new T(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...));
976 }
977
978
979} // end namespace Detail
980} // end namespace Catch
981
982#endif // CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED

1328#ifndef CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1329#define CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1330
1331namespace Catch {
1332 namespace Benchmark {
1333 struct OutlierClassification {
1334 int samples_seen = 0;
1335 int low_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR below Q1
1336 int low_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR below Q1
1337 int high_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR above Q3
1338 int high_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR above Q3
1339
1340 constexpr int total() const {
1341 return low_severe + low_mild + high_mild + high_severe;
1342 }
1343 };
1344 } // namespace Benchmark
1345} // namespace Catch
1346
1347#endif // CATCH_OUTLIERS_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED

1377 };

1430#ifndef CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED
1431#define CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED
1432
1433#if defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)
1434# include <atomic> // atomic_thread_fence
1435#endif
1436
1437
1438#include <type_traits>
1439
1440namespace Catch {
1441 namespace Benchmark {
1442#if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
1443 template <typename T>
1444 inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1445 asm volatile("" : : "g"(p) : "memory");
1446 }
1447 inline void keep_memory() {
1448 asm volatile("" : : : "memory");
1449 }
1450
1451 namespace Detail {
1452 inline void optimizer_barrier() { keep_memory(); }
1453 } // namespace Detail
1454#elif defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)
1455
1456#if defined(_MSVC_VER)
1457#pragma optimize("", off)
1458#elif defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__)
1459// For IAR the pragma only affects the following function
1460#pragma optimize=disable
1461#endif
1462 template <typename T>
1463 inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1464 // thanks @milleniumbug
1465 *reinterpret_cast<char volatile*>(p) = *reinterpret_cast<char const volatile*>(p);
1466 }
1467 // TODO equivalent keep_memory()
1468#if defined(_MSVC_VER)
1469#pragma optimize("", on)
1470#endif
1471
1472 namespace Detail {
1473 inline void optimizer_barrier() {
1474 std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
1475 }
1476 } // namespace Detail
1477
1478#endif
1479
1480 template <typename T>
1481 inline void deoptimize_value(T&& x) {
1482 keep_memory(&x);
1483 }
1484
1485 template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1486 inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value> {
1487 deoptimize_value(CATCH_FORWARD(fn) (CATCH_FORWARD(args)...));
1488 }
1489
1490 template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1491 inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> std::enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value> {
1492 CATCH_FORWARD((fn)) (CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1493 }
1494 } // namespace Benchmark
1495} // namespace Catch
1496
1497#endif // CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED

1505namespace Catch {
1506 template <typename>
1507 struct true_given : std::true_type {};
1508
1509 struct is_callable_tester {
1510 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1511 static true_given<decltype(std::declval<Fun>()(std::declval<Args>()...))> test(int);
1512 template <typename...>
1513 static std::false_type test(...);
1514 };
1515
1516 template <typename T>
1517 struct is_callable;
1518
1519 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1520 struct is_callable<Fun(Args...)> : decltype(is_callable_tester::test<Fun, Args...>(0)) {};
1521
1522
1523#if defined(__cpp_lib_is_invocable) && __cpp_lib_is_invocable >= 201703
1524 // std::result_of is deprecated in C++17 and removed in C++20. Hence, it is
1525 // replaced with std::invoke_result here.
1526 template <typename Func, typename... U>
1527 using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::invoke_result_t<Func, U...>>>;
1528#else
1529 template <typename Func, typename... U>
1530 using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::result_of_t<Func(U...)>>>;
1531#endif
1532
1533} // namespace Catch

1536 struct na;

1541namespace Catch {
1542 namespace Benchmark {
1543 namespace Detail {
1544 struct ChronometerConcept {
1545 virtual void start() = 0;
1546 virtual void finish() = 0;
1547 virtual ~ChronometerConcept(); // = default;
1548
1549 ChronometerConcept() = default;
1550 ChronometerConcept(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1551 ChronometerConcept& operator=(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1552 };
1553 template <typename Clock>
1554 struct ChronometerModel final : public ChronometerConcept {
1555 void start() override { started = Clock::now(); }
1556 void finish() override { finished = Clock::now(); }
1557
1558 IDuration elapsed() const {
1559 return std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::nanoseconds>(
1560 finished - started );
1561 }
1562
1563 TimePoint<Clock> started;
1564 TimePoint<Clock> finished;
1565 };
1566 } // namespace Detail
1567
1568 struct Chronometer {
1569 public:
1570 template <typename Fun>
1571 void measure(Fun&& fun) { measure(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), is_callable<Fun(int)>()); }
1572
1573 int runs() const { return repeats; }
1574
1575 Chronometer(Detail::ChronometerConcept& meter, int repeats_)
1576 : impl(&meter)
1577 , repeats(repeats_) {}
1578
1579 private:
1580 template <typename Fun>
1581 void measure(Fun&& fun, std::false_type) {
1582 measure([&fun](int) { return fun(); }, std::true_type());
1583 }
1584
1585 template <typename Fun>
1586 void measure(Fun&& fun, std::true_type) {
1587 Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1588 impl->start();
1589 for (int i = 0; i < repeats; ++i) invoke_deoptimized(fun, i);
1590 impl->finish();
1591 Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1592 }
1593
1594 Detail::ChronometerConcept* impl;
1595 int repeats;
1596 };
1597 } // namespace Benchmark
1598} // namespace Catch
1599
1600#endif // CATCH_CHRONOMETER_HPP_INCLUDED
1601
1602#include <type_traits>
1603
1604namespace Catch {
1605 namespace Benchmark {
1606 namespace Detail {
1607 template <typename T, typename U>
1608 static constexpr bool is_related_v = std::is_same<std::decay_t<T>, std::decay_t<U>>::value;
1609
1617 struct BenchmarkFunction {
1618 private:
1619 struct callable {
1620 virtual void call(Chronometer meter) const = 0;
1621 virtual ~callable(); // = default;
1622
1623 callable() = default;
1624 callable(callable&&) = default;
1625 callable& operator=(callable&&) = default;
1626 };
1627 template <typename Fun>
1628 struct model : public callable {
1629 model(Fun&& fun_) : fun(CATCH_MOVE(fun_)) {}
1630 model(Fun const& fun_) : fun(fun_) {}
1631
1632 void call(Chronometer meter) const override {
1633 call(meter, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
1634 }
1635 void call(Chronometer meter, std::true_type) const {
1636 fun(meter);
1637 }
1638 void call(Chronometer meter, std::false_type) const {
1639 meter.measure(fun);
1640 }
1641
1642 Fun fun;
1643 };
1644
1645 public:
1646 BenchmarkFunction();
1647
1648 template <typename Fun,
1649 std::enable_if_t<!is_related_v<Fun, BenchmarkFunction>, int> = 0>
1650 BenchmarkFunction(Fun&& fun)
1651 : f(new model<std::decay_t<Fun>>(CATCH_FORWARD(fun))) {}
1652
1653 BenchmarkFunction( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept:
1654 f( CATCH_MOVE( that.f ) ) {}
1655
1656 BenchmarkFunction&
1657 operator=( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept {
1658 f = CATCH_MOVE( that.f );
1659 return *this;
1660 }
1661
1662 void operator()(Chronometer meter) const { f->call(meter); }
1663
1664 private:
1665 Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> f;
1666 };
1667 } // namespace Detail
1668 } // namespace Benchmark
1669} // namespace Catch
1670
1671#endif // CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED

1684 template <typename Fun>
1685 struct repeater {
1686 void operator()(int k) const {
1687 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
1688 fun();
1689 }
1690 }
1691 Fun fun;
1692 };
1693 template <typename Fun>
1694 repeater<std::decay_t<Fun>> repeat(Fun&& fun) {
1695 return { CATCH_FORWARD(fun) };
1696 }

1720#ifndef CATCH_COMPLETE_INVOKE_HPP_INCLUDED
1721#define CATCH_COMPLETE_INVOKE_HPP_INCLUDED
1722
1723
1724namespace Catch {
1725 namespace Benchmark {
1726 namespace Detail {
1727 template <typename T>
1728 struct CompleteType { using type = T; };
1729 template <>
1730 struct CompleteType<void> { struct type {}; };
1731
1732 template <typename T>
1733 using CompleteType_t = typename CompleteType<T>::type;
1734
1735 template <typename Result>
1736 struct CompleteInvoker {
1737 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1738 static Result invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1739 return CATCH_FORWARD(fun)(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1740 }
1741 };
1742 template <>
1743 struct CompleteInvoker<void> {
1744 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1745 static CompleteType_t<void> invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1746 CATCH_FORWARD(fun)(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1747 return {};
1748 }
1749 };
1750
1751 // invoke and not return void :(
1752 template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1753 CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>> complete_invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1754 return CompleteInvoker<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>>::invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1755 }
1756
1757 } // namespace Detail
1758
1759 template <typename Fun>
1760 Detail::CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun>> user_code(Fun&& fun) {
1761 return Detail::complete_invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun));
1762 }
1763 } // namespace Benchmark
1764} // namespace Catch
1765
1766#endif // CATCH_COMPLETE_INVOKE_HPP_INCLUDED

1775namespace Catch {
1776 namespace Benchmark {
1777 template <typename Result>
1778 struct Timing {
1779 IDuration elapsed;
1780 Result result;
1781 int iterations;
1782 };
1783 template <typename Func, typename... Args>
1784 using TimingOf = Timing<Detail::CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Func, Args...>>>;
1785 } // namespace Benchmark
1786} // namespace Catch
1787
1788#endif // CATCH_TIMING_HPP_INCLUDED

1790namespace Catch {
1791 namespace Benchmark {
1792 namespace Detail {
1793 template <typename Clock, typename Fun, typename... Args>
1794 TimingOf<Fun, Args...> measure(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1795 auto start = Clock::now();
1796 auto&& r = Detail::complete_invoke(CATCH_FORWARD(fun), CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
1797 auto end = Clock::now();
1798 auto delta = end - start;
1799 return { delta, CATCH_FORWARD(r), 1 };
1800 }
1801 } // namespace Detail
1802 } // namespace Benchmark
1803} // namespace Catch
1804
1805#endif // CATCH_MEASURE_HPP_INCLUDED
1806
1807#include <type_traits>
1808
1809namespace Catch {
1810 namespace Benchmark {
1811 namespace Detail {
1812 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1813 TimingOf<Fun, int> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::false_type) {
1814 return Detail::measure<Clock>(fun, iters);
1815 }
1816 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1817 TimingOf<Fun, Chronometer> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::true_type) {
1818 Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> meter;
1819 auto&& result = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, Chronometer(meter, iters));
1820
1821 return { meter.elapsed(), CATCH_MOVE(result), iters };
1822 }
1823
1824 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1825 using run_for_at_least_argument_t = std::conditional_t<is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>::value, Chronometer, int>;
1826
1827
1828 [[noreturn]]
1829 void throw_optimized_away_error();
1830
1831 template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
1832 TimingOf<Fun, run_for_at_least_argument_t<Clock, Fun>>
1833 run_for_at_least(IDuration how_long,
1834 const int initial_iterations,
1835 Fun&& fun) {
1836 auto iters = initial_iterations;
1837 while (iters < (1 << 30)) {
1838 auto&& Timing = measure_one<Clock>(fun, iters, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
1839
1840 if (Timing.elapsed >= how_long) {
1841 return { Timing.elapsed, CATCH_MOVE(Timing.result), iters };
1842 }
1843 iters *= 2;
1844 }
1845 throw_optimized_away_error();
1846 }
1847 } // namespace Detail
1848 } // namespace Benchmark
1849} // namespace Catch
1850
1851#endif // CATCH_RUN_FOR_AT_LEAST_HPP_INCLUDED
1852
1853#include <vector>
1854
1855namespace Catch {
1856 namespace Benchmark {
1857 struct ExecutionPlan {
1858 int iterations_per_sample;
1859 FDuration estimated_duration;
1860 Detail::BenchmarkFunction benchmark;
1861 FDuration warmup_time;
1862 int warmup_iterations;
1863
1864 template <typename Clock>
1865 std::vector<FDuration> run(const IConfig &cfg, Environment env) const {
1866 // warmup a bit
1867 Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(
1868 std::chrono::duration_cast<IDuration>( warmup_time ),
1869 warmup_iterations,
1870 Detail::repeat( []() { return Clock::now(); } )
1871 );
1872
1873 std::vector<FDuration> times;
1874 const auto num_samples = cfg.benchmarkSamples();
1875 times.reserve( num_samples );
1876 for ( size_t i = 0; i < num_samples; ++i ) {
1877 Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> model;
1878 this->benchmark( Chronometer( model, iterations_per_sample ) );
1879 auto sample_time = model.elapsed() - env.clock_cost.mean;
1880 if ( sample_time < FDuration::zero() ) {
1881 sample_time = FDuration::zero();
1882 }
1883 times.push_back(sample_time / iterations_per_sample);
1884 }
1885 return times;
1886 }
1887 };
1888 } // namespace Benchmark
1889} // namespace Catch
1890
1891#endif // CATCH_EXECUTION_PLAN_HPP_INCLUDED

1953#include <algorithm>
1954#include <vector>
1955#include <cmath>
1956
1957namespace Catch {
1958 namespace Benchmark {
1959 namespace Detail {
1960 template <typename Clock>
1961 std::vector<double> resolution(int k) {
1962 const size_t points = static_cast<size_t>( k + 1 );
1963 // To avoid overhead from the branch inside vector::push_back,
1964 // we allocate them all and then overwrite.
1965 std::vector<TimePoint<Clock>> times(points);
1966 for ( auto& time : times ) {
1967 time = Clock::now();
1968 }
1969
1970 std::vector<double> deltas;
1971 deltas.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(k));
1972 for ( size_t idx = 1; idx < points; ++idx ) {
1973 deltas.push_back( static_cast<double>(
1974 ( times[idx] - times[idx - 1] ).count() ) );
1975 }
1976
1977 return deltas;
1978 }
1979
1980 constexpr auto warmup_iterations = 10000;
1981 constexpr auto warmup_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(100);
1982 constexpr auto minimum_ticks = 1000;
1983 constexpr auto warmup_seed = 10000;
1984 constexpr auto clock_resolution_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(500);
1985 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_time_limit = std::chrono::seconds(1);
1986 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit = 100000;
1987 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(10);
1988 constexpr auto clock_cost_estimation_iterations = 10000;
1989
1990 template <typename Clock>
1991 int warmup() {
1992 return run_for_at_least<Clock>(warmup_time, warmup_seed, &resolution<Clock>)
1993 .iterations;
1994 }
1995 template <typename Clock>
1996 EnvironmentEstimate estimate_clock_resolution(int iterations) {
1997 auto r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(clock_resolution_estimation_time, iterations, &resolution<Clock>)
1998 .result;
1999 return {
2000 FDuration(mean(r.data(), r.data() + r.size())),
2001 classify_outliers(r.data(), r.data() + r.size()),
2002 };
2003 }
2004 template <typename Clock>
2005 EnvironmentEstimate estimate_clock_cost(FDuration resolution) {
2006 auto time_limit = (std::min)(
2007 resolution * clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit,
2008 FDuration(clock_cost_estimation_time_limit));
2009 auto time_clock = [](int k) {
2010 return Detail::measure<Clock>([k] {
2011 for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
2012 volatile auto ignored = Clock::now();
2013 (void)ignored;
2014 }
2015 }).elapsed;
2016 };
2017 time_clock(1);
2018 int iters = clock_cost_estimation_iterations;
2019 auto&& r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(clock_cost_estimation_time, iters, time_clock);
2020 std::vector<double> times;
2021 int nsamples = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(time_limit / r.elapsed));
2022 times.reserve(static_cast<size_t>(nsamples));
2023 for ( int s = 0; s < nsamples; ++s ) {
2024 times.push_back( static_cast<double>(
2025 ( time_clock( r.iterations ) / r.iterations )
2026 .count() ) );
2027 }
2028 return {
2029 FDuration(mean(times.data(), times.data() + times.size())),
2030 classify_outliers(times.data(), times.data() + times.size()),
2031 };
2032 }
2033
2034 template <typename Clock>
2035 Environment measure_environment() {
2036#if defined(__clang__)
2037# pragma clang diagnostic push
2038# pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wexit-time-destructors"
2039#endif
2040 static Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<Environment> env;
2041#if defined(__clang__)
2042# pragma clang diagnostic pop
2043#endif
2044 if (env) {
2045 return *env;
2046 }
2047
2048 auto iters = Detail::warmup<Clock>();
2049 auto resolution = Detail::estimate_clock_resolution<Clock>(iters);
2050 auto cost = Detail::estimate_clock_cost<Clock>(resolution.mean);
2051
2052 env = Catch::Detail::make_unique<Environment>( Environment{resolution, cost} );
2053 return *env;
2054 }
2055 } // namespace Detail
2056 } // namespace Benchmark
2057} // namespace Catch
2058
2059#endif // CATCH_ESTIMATE_CLOCK_HPP_INCLUDED

2104#include <algorithm>
2105#include <chrono>
2106#include <exception>
2107#include <string>
2108#include <cmath>
2109
2110namespace Catch {
2111 namespace Benchmark {
2112 struct Benchmark {
2113 Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName)
2114 : name(CATCH_MOVE(benchmarkName)) {}
2115
2116 template <class FUN>
2117 Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName , FUN &&func)
2118 : fun(CATCH_MOVE(func)), name(CATCH_MOVE(benchmarkName)) {}
2119
2120 template <typename Clock>
2121 ExecutionPlan prepare(const IConfig &cfg, Environment env) {
2122 auto min_time = env.clock_resolution.mean * Detail::minimum_ticks;
2123 auto run_time = std::max(min_time, std::chrono::duration_cast<decltype(min_time)>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()));
2124 auto&& test = Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<IDuration>(run_time), 1, fun);
2125 int new_iters = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(min_time * test.iterations / test.elapsed));
2126 return { new_iters, test.elapsed / test.iterations * new_iters * cfg.benchmarkSamples(), CATCH_MOVE(fun), std::chrono::duration_cast<FDuration>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()), Detail::warmup_iterations };
2127 }
2128
2129 template <typename Clock = default_clock>
2130 void run() {
2131 static_assert( Clock::is_steady,
2132 "Benchmarking clock should be steady" );
2133 auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2134
2135 auto env = Detail::measure_environment<Clock>();
2136
2137 getResultCapture().benchmarkPreparing(name);
2138 CATCH_TRY{
2139 auto plan = user_code([&] {
2140 return prepare<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2141 });
2142
2143 BenchmarkInfo info {
2144 CATCH_MOVE(name),
2145 plan.estimated_duration.count(),
2146 plan.iterations_per_sample,
2147 cfg->benchmarkSamples(),
2148 cfg->benchmarkResamples(),
2149 env.clock_resolution.mean.count(),
2150 env.clock_cost.mean.count()
2151 };
2152
2153 getResultCapture().benchmarkStarting(info);
2154
2155 auto samples = user_code([&] {
2156 return plan.template run<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2157 });
2158
2159 auto analysis = Detail::analyse(*cfg, samples.data(), samples.data() + samples.size());
2160 BenchmarkStats<> stats{ CATCH_MOVE(info), CATCH_MOVE(analysis.samples), analysis.mean, analysis.standard_deviation, analysis.outliers, analysis.outlier_variance };
2161 getResultCapture().benchmarkEnded(stats);
2162 } CATCH_CATCH_ALL {
2163 getResultCapture().benchmarkFailed(translateActiveException());
2164 // We let the exception go further up so that the
2165 // test case is marked as failed.
2166 std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
2167 }
2168 }
2169
2170 // sets lambda to be used in fun *and* executes benchmark!
2171 template <typename Fun, std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_related_v<Fun, Benchmark>, int> = 0>
2172 Benchmark & operator=(Fun func) {
2173 auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2174 if (!cfg->skipBenchmarks()) {
2175 fun = Detail::BenchmarkFunction(func);
2176 run();
2177 }
2178 return *this;
2179 }
2180
2181 explicit operator bool() {
2182 return true;
2183 }
2184
2185 private:
2186 Detail::BenchmarkFunction fun;
2187 std::string name;
2188 };
2189 }
2190} // namespace Catch
2191
2192#define INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_1_ARG(arg1, arg2, ...) arg1
2193#define INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_2_ARG(arg1, arg2, ...) arg2
2194
2195#define INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK(BenchmarkName, name, benchmarkIndex)\
2196 if( Catch::Benchmark::Benchmark BenchmarkName{name} ) \
2197 BenchmarkName = [&](int benchmarkIndex)
2198
2199#define INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(BenchmarkName, name)\
2200 if( Catch::Benchmark::Benchmark BenchmarkName{name} ) \
2201 BenchmarkName = [&]
2202
2203#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL)
2204
2205#define CATCH_BENCHMARK(...) \
2206 INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(CATCH2_INTERNAL_BENCHMARK_), INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_1_ARG(__VA_ARGS__,,), INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_2_ARG(__VA_ARGS__,,))
2207#define CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(name) \
2208 INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(CATCH2_INTERNAL_BENCHMARK_), name)
2209
2210#else
2211
2212#define BENCHMARK(...) \
2213 INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(CATCH2_INTERNAL_BENCHMARK_), INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_1_ARG(__VA_ARGS__,,), INTERNAL_CATCH_GET_2_ARG(__VA_ARGS__,,))
2214#define BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(name) \

2224#ifndef CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED
2225#define CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED

2227
2228#include <type_traits>
2229
2230namespace Catch {
2231 namespace Benchmark {
2232 namespace Detail {
2233 template <typename T, bool Destruct>
2234 struct ObjectStorage
2235 {
2236 ObjectStorage() = default;
2237
2238 ObjectStorage(const ObjectStorage& other)
2239 {
2240 new(&data) T(other.stored_object());
2241 }
2242
2243 ObjectStorage(ObjectStorage&& other)
2244 {
2245 new(data) T(CATCH_MOVE(other.stored_object()));
2246 }
2247
2248 ~ObjectStorage() { destruct_on_exit<T>(); }
2249
2250 template <typename... Args>
2251 void construct(Args&&... args)
2252 {
2253 new (data) T(CATCH_FORWARD(args)...);
2254 }
2255
2256 template <bool AllowManualDestruction = !Destruct>
2257 std::enable_if_t<AllowManualDestruction> destruct()
2258 {
2259 stored_object().~T();
2260 }
2261
2262 private:
2263 // If this is a constructor benchmark, destruct the underlying object
2264 template <typename U>
2265 void destruct_on_exit(std::enable_if_t<Destruct, U>* = nullptr) { destruct<true>(); }
2266 // Otherwise, don't
2267 template <typename U>
2268 void destruct_on_exit(std::enable_if_t<!Destruct, U>* = nullptr) { }
2269
2270#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && __GNUC__ <= 6
2271# pragma GCC diagnostic push
2272# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wstrict-aliasing"
2273#endif
2274 T& stored_object() { return *reinterpret_cast<T*>( data ); }
2275
2276 T const& stored_object() const {
2277 return *reinterpret_cast<T const*>( data );
2278 }
2279#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && __GNUC__ <= 6
2280# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2281#endif
2282
2283 alignas( T ) unsigned char data[sizeof( T )]{};
2284 };
2285 } // namespace Detail
2286
2287 template <typename T>
2288 using storage_for = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, true>;
2289
2290 template <typename T>
2291 using destructable_object = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, false>;
2292 } // namespace Benchmark
2293} // namespace Catch
2294
2295#endif // CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED

2353
2354namespace Catch {
2355
2356 class ReusableStringStream : Detail::NonCopyable {
2357 std::size_t m_index;
2358 std::ostream* m_oss;
2359 public:
2360 ReusableStringStream();
2361 ~ReusableStringStream();
2362
2364 std::string str() const;
2366 void str(std::string const& str);
2367
2368#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
2369#pragma GCC diagnostic push
2370// Old versions of GCC do not understand -Wnonnull-compare
2371#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wpragmas"
2372// Streaming a function pointer triggers Waddress and Wnonnull-compare
2373// on GCC, because it implicitly converts it to bool and then decides
2374// that the check it uses (a? true : false) is tautological and cannot
2375// be null...
2376#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Waddress"
2377#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wnonnull-compare"
2378#endif
2379
2380 template<typename T>
2381 auto operator << ( T const& value ) -> ReusableStringStream& {
2382 *m_oss << value;
2383 return *this;
2384 }
2385
2386#if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
2387#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
2388#endif
2389 auto get() -> std::ostream& { return *m_oss; }
2390 };
2391}
2392
2393#endif // CATCH_REUSABLE_STRING_STREAM_HPP_INCLUDED

2434
2435 class IMutableEnumValuesRegistry {
2436 public:
2437 virtual ~IMutableEnumValuesRegistry(); // = default;
2438
2439 virtual Detail::EnumInfo const& registerEnum( StringRef enumName, StringRef allEnums, std::vector<int> const& values ) = 0;
2440
2441 template<typename E>
2442 Detail::EnumInfo const& registerEnum( StringRef enumName, StringRef allEnums, std::initializer_list<E> values ) {
2443 static_assert(sizeof(int) >= sizeof(E), "Cannot serialize enum to int");
2444 std::vector<int> intValues;
2445 intValues.reserve( values.size() );
2446 for( auto enumValue : values )
2447 intValues.push_back( static_cast<int>( enumValue ) );
2448 return registerEnum( enumName, allEnums, intValues );
2449 }
2450 };

2476 inline std::size_t catch_strnlen(const char *str, std::size_t n) {
2477 auto ret = std::char_traits<char>::find(str, n, '\0');
2478 if (ret != nullptr) {
2479 return static_cast<std::size_t>(ret - str);
2480 }
2481 return n;
2482 }

2500 template<typename T,typename = void>
2501 static constexpr bool IsStreamInsertable_v = false;
2502
2503 template <typename T>
2504 static constexpr bool IsStreamInsertable_v<
2505 T,
2506 decltype( void( std::declval<std::ostream&>() << std::declval<T>() ) )> =
2507 true;
2508
2509 template<typename E>
2510 std::string convertUnknownEnumToString( E e );
2511

2513 std::enable_if_t<
2514 !std::is_enum<T>::value && !std::is_base_of<std::exception, T>::value,
2515 std::string> convertUnstreamable( T const& ) {
2516 return std::string(Detail::unprintableString);
2517 }
2518 template<typename T>
2519 std::enable_if_t<
2520 !std::is_enum<T>::value && std::is_base_of<std::exception, T>::value,
2521 std::string> convertUnstreamable(T const& ex) {
2522 return ex.what();
2523 }

2527 std::enable_if_t<
2528 std::is_enum<T>::value,
2529 std::string> convertUnstreamable( T const& value ) {
2530 return convertUnknownEnumToString( value );
2531 }

2533#if defined(_MANAGED)
2535 template<typename T>
2536 std::string clrReferenceToString( T^ ref ) {
2537 if (ref == nullptr)
2538 return std::string("null");
2539 auto bytes = System::Text::Encoding::UTF8->GetBytes(ref->ToString());
2540 cli::pin_ptr<System::Byte> p = &bytes[0];
2541 return std::string(reinterpret_cast<char const *>(p), bytes->Length);
2542 }

2548 template <typename T, typename = void>
2549 struct StringMaker {
2550 template <typename Fake = T>
2551 static
2552 std::enable_if_t<::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable_v<Fake>, std::string>
2553 convert(const Fake& value) {
2554 ReusableStringStream rss;
2555 // NB: call using the function-like syntax to avoid ambiguity with
2556 // user-defined templated operator<< under clang.
2557 rss.operator<<(value);
2558 return rss.str();
2559 }
2560
2561 template <typename Fake = T>
2562 static
2563 std::enable_if_t<!::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable_v<Fake>, std::string>
2564 convert( const Fake& value ) {
2565#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER)
2566 return Detail::convertUnstreamable(value);
2567#else
2568 return CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER(value);
2569#endif
2570 }
2571 };
2572
2573 namespace Detail {
2574
2575 std::string makeExceptionHappenedString();
2576
2577 // This function dispatches all stringification requests inside of Catch.
2578 // Should be preferably called fully qualified, like ::Catch::Detail::stringify
2579 template <typename T>
2580 std::string stringify( const T& e ) {
2581 CATCH_TRY {
2582 return ::Catch::StringMaker<
2583 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>>::convert( e );
2584 }
2585 CATCH_CATCH_ALL { return makeExceptionHappenedString(); }
2586 }
2587
2588 template<typename E>
2589 std::string convertUnknownEnumToString( E e ) {
2590 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(static_cast<std::underlying_type_t<E>>(e));
2591 }
2592
2593#if defined(_MANAGED)
2594 template <typename T>
2595 std::string stringify( T^ e ) {
2596 return ::Catch::StringMaker<T^>::convert(e);
2597 }
2598#endif

2776 namespace Detail {
2777 template<typename InputIterator, typename Sentinel = InputIterator>
2778 std::string rangeToString(InputIterator first, Sentinel last) {
2779 ReusableStringStream rss;
2780 rss << "{ ";
2781 if (first != last) {
2782 rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
2783 for (++first; first != last; ++first)
2784 rss << ", " << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
2785 }
2786 rss << " }";
2787 return rss.str();
2788 }
2789 }
2790
2791} // namespace Catch

2809 struct StringMaker<std::pair<T1, T2> > {
2810 static std::string convert(const std::pair<T1, T2>& pair) {
2811 ReusableStringStream rss;
2812 rss << "{ "
2813 << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(pair.first)
2814 << ", "

2826 template<typename T>
2827 struct StringMaker<std::optional<T> > {

2829 if (optional.has_value()) {
2830 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*optional);
2831 } else {
2832 return "{ }";
2833 }

2845// Separate std::tuple specialization
2846#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_ENABLE_TUPLE_STRINGMAKER)
2847#include <tuple>
2848namespace Catch {
2849 namespace Detail {
2850 template<
2851 typename Tuple,
2852 std::size_t N = 0,
2853 bool = (N < std::tuple_size<Tuple>::value)
2854 >
2855 struct TupleElementPrinter {
2856 static void print(const Tuple& tuple, std::ostream& os) {
2857 os << (N ? ", " : " ")
2858 << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(std::get<N>(tuple));
2859 TupleElementPrinter<Tuple, N + 1>::print(tuple, os);
2860 }
2861 };
2862
2863 template<
2864 typename Tuple,
2865 std::size_t N
2866 >
2867 struct TupleElementPrinter<Tuple, N, false> {
2868 static void print(const Tuple&, std::ostream&) {}
2869 };
2870
2871 }
2872
2873
2874 template<typename ...Types>
2875 struct StringMaker<std::tuple<Types...>> {
2876 static std::string convert(const std::tuple<Types...>& tuple) {
2877 ReusableStringStream rss;
2878 rss << '{';
2879 Detail::TupleElementPrinter<std::tuple<Types...>>::print(tuple, rss.get());
2880 rss << " }";
2881 return rss.str();
2882 }
2883 };
2884}

2887#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_ENABLE_VARIANT_STRINGMAKER) && defined(CATCH_CONFIG_CPP17_VARIANT)
2888#include <variant>
2889namespace Catch {
2890 template<>
2891 struct StringMaker<std::monostate> {
2892 static std::string convert(const std::monostate&) {
2893 return "{ }";
2894 }
2895 };
2896
2897 template<typename... Elements>
2898 struct StringMaker<std::variant<Elements...>> {
2899 static std::string convert(const std::variant<Elements...>& variant) {
2900 if (variant.valueless_by_exception()) {
2901 return "{valueless variant}";
2902 } else {
2903 return std::visit(
2904 [](const auto& value) {
2905 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(value);
2906 },
2907 variant
2908 );
2909 }
2910 }
2911 };
2912}
2913#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_ENABLE_VARIANT_STRINGMAKER

2915namespace Catch {
2916 // Import begin/ end from std here
2917 using std::begin;
2918 using std::end;
2919
2920 namespace Detail {
2921 template <typename T, typename = void>
2922 struct is_range_impl : std::false_type {};
2923
2924 template <typename T>
2925 struct is_range_impl<T, void_t<decltype(begin(std::declval<T>()))>> : std::true_type {};
2926 } // namespace Detail
2927
2928 template <typename T>
2929 struct is_range : Detail::is_range_impl<T> {};
2930
2931#if defined(_MANAGED) // Managed types are never ranges
2932 template <typename T>
2933 struct is_range<T^> {
2934 static const bool value = false;
2935 };
2936#endif
2937
2938 template<typename Range>
2939 std::string rangeToString( Range const& range ) {
2940 return ::Catch::Detail::rangeToString( begin( range ), end( range ) );
2941 }
2942
2943 // Handle vector<bool> specially
2944 template<typename Allocator>
2945 std::string rangeToString( std::vector<bool, Allocator> const& v ) {
2946 ReusableStringStream rss;
2947 rss << "{ ";
2948 bool first = true;
2949 for( bool b : v ) {
2950 if( first )
2951 first = false;
2952 else
2953 rss << ", ";
2954 rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify( b );
2955 }
2956 rss << " }";
2957 return rss.str();
2958 }
2959
2960 template<typename R>
2961 struct StringMaker<R, std::enable_if_t<is_range<R>::value && !::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable_v<R>>> {
2962 static std::string convert( R const& range ) {
2963 return rangeToString( range );
2964 }
2965 };
2966
2967 template <typename T, size_t SZ>
2968 struct StringMaker<T[SZ]> {
2969 static std::string convert(T const(&arr)[SZ]) {
2970 return rangeToString(arr);
2971 }
2972 };
2973
2974
2975} // namespace Catch

2985template <class Ratio>
2986struct ratio_string {
2987 static std::string symbol() {
2988 Catch::ReusableStringStream rss;
2989 rss << '[' << Ratio::num << '/'
2990 << Ratio::den << ']';
2991 return rss.str();
2992 }
2993};
2994
2995template <>
2996struct ratio_string<std::atto> {
2997 static char symbol() { return 'a'; }
2998};
2999template <>
3000struct ratio_string<std::femto> {
3001 static char symbol() { return 'f'; }
3002};
3003template <>
3004struct ratio_string<std::pico> {
3005 static char symbol() { return 'p'; }
3006};
3007template <>
3008struct ratio_string<std::nano> {
3009 static char symbol() { return 'n'; }
3010};
3011template <>
3012struct ratio_string<std::micro> {
3013 static char symbol() { return 'u'; }
3014};
3015template <>
3016struct ratio_string<std::milli> {
3017 static char symbol() { return 'm'; }
3018};

3021 // std::chrono::duration specializations
3022 template<typename Value, typename Ratio>
3023 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::duration<Value, Ratio>> {
3024 static std::string convert(std::chrono::duration<Value, Ratio> const& duration) {
3025 ReusableStringStream rss;
3026 rss << duration.count() << ' ' << ratio_string<Ratio>::symbol() << 's';
3027 return rss.str();
3028 }
3029 };
3030 template<typename Value>
3031 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<1>>> {
3032 static std::string convert(std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<1>> const& duration) {
3033 ReusableStringStream rss;
3034 rss << duration.count() << " s";
3035 return rss.str();
3036 }
3037 };
3038 template<typename Value>
3039 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<60>>> {
3040 static std::string convert(std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<60>> const& duration) {
3041 ReusableStringStream rss;
3042 rss << duration.count() << " m";
3043 return rss.str();
3044 }
3045 };
3046 template<typename Value>
3047 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<3600>>> {
3048 static std::string convert(std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<3600>> const& duration) {
3049 ReusableStringStream rss;
3050 rss << duration.count() << " h";
3051 return rss.str();
3052 }
3053 };
3054
3056 // std::chrono::time_point specialization
3057 // Generic time_point cannot be specialized, only std::chrono::time_point<system_clock>
3058 template<typename Clock, typename Duration>
3059 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration>> {
3060 static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3061 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(time_point.time_since_epoch()) + " since epoch";
3062 }
3063 };
3064 // std::chrono::time_point<system_clock> specialization
3065 template<typename Duration>
3066 struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration>> {
3067 static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3068 const auto systemish = std::chrono::time_point_cast<
3069 std::chrono::system_clock::duration>( time_point );
3070 const auto as_time_t = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t( systemish );
3071
3072#ifdef _MSC_VER
3073 std::tm timeInfo = {};
3074 const auto err = gmtime_s( &timeInfo, &as_time_t );
3075 if ( err ) {
3076 return "gmtime from provided timepoint has failed. This "
3077 "happens e.g. with pre-1970 dates using Microsoft libc";
3078 }
3079#else
3080 std::tm* timeInfo = std::gmtime( &as_time_t );
3081#endif
3082
3083 auto const timeStampSize = sizeof("2017-01-16T17:06:45Z");
3084 char timeStamp[timeStampSize];
3085 const char * const fmt = "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ";
3086
3087#ifdef _MSC_VER
3088 std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, &timeInfo);
3089#else
3090 std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, timeInfo);
3091#endif
3092 return std::string(timeStamp, timeStampSize - 1);
3093 }
3094 };
3095}

3102 static const auto& enumInfo = ::Catch::getMutableRegistryHub().getMutableEnumValuesRegistry().registerEnum( #enumName, #__VA_ARGS__, { __VA_ARGS__ } ); \
3103 return static_cast<std::string>(enumInfo.lookup( static_cast<int>( value ) )); \
3104 } \
3105 }; \

3120 class Approx {
3121 private:
3122 bool equalityComparisonImpl(double other) const;
3123 // Sets and validates the new margin (margin >= 0)
3124 void setMargin(double margin);
3125 // Sets and validates the new epsilon (0 < epsilon < 1)
3126 void setEpsilon(double epsilon);
3127
3128 public:
3129 explicit Approx ( double value );
3130
3131 static Approx custom();
3132
3133 Approx operator-() const;
3134
3135 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3136 Approx operator()( T const& value ) const {
3137 Approx approx( static_cast<double>(value) );
3138 approx.m_epsilon = m_epsilon;
3139 approx.m_margin = m_margin;
3140 approx.m_scale = m_scale;
3141 return approx;
3142 }
3143
3144 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3145 explicit Approx( T const& value ): Approx(static_cast<double>(value))
3146 {}
3147
3148
3149 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3150 friend bool operator == ( const T& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3151 auto lhs_v = static_cast<double>(lhs);
3152 return rhs.equalityComparisonImpl(lhs_v);
3153 }
3154
3155 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3156 friend bool operator == ( Approx const& lhs, const T& rhs ) {
3157 return operator==( rhs, lhs );
3158 }
3159
3160 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3161 friend bool operator != ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3162 return !operator==( lhs, rhs );
3163 }
3164
3165 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3166 friend bool operator != ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3167 return !operator==( rhs, lhs );
3168 }
3169
3170 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3171 friend bool operator <= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3172 return static_cast<double>(lhs) < rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3173 }
3174
3175 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3176 friend bool operator <= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3177 return lhs.m_value < static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3178 }
3179
3180 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3181 friend bool operator >= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3182 return static_cast<double>(lhs) > rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3183 }
3184
3185 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3186 friend bool operator >= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3187 return lhs.m_value > static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3188 }
3189
3190 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3191 Approx& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
3192 const auto epsilonAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newEpsilon);
3193 setEpsilon(epsilonAsDouble);
3194 return *this;
3195 }
3196
3197 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3198 Approx& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
3199 const auto marginAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newMargin);
3200 setMargin(marginAsDouble);
3201 return *this;
3202 }
3203
3204 template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3205 Approx& scale( T const& newScale ) {
3206 m_scale = static_cast<double>(newScale);
3207 return *this;
3208 }
3209
3210 std::string toString() const;
3211
3212 private:
3213 double m_epsilon;
3214 double m_margin;
3215 double m_scale;
3216 double m_value;
3217 };

3532#ifndef CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED
3533#define CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED
3534
3535
3536#include <cassert>
3537
3538namespace Catch {
3539
3540 // An optional type
3541 template<typename T>
3542 class Optional {
3543 public:
3544 Optional(): nullableValue( nullptr ) {}
3545 ~Optional() { reset(); }
3546
3547 Optional( T const& _value ):
3548 nullableValue( new ( storage ) T( _value ) ) {}
3549 Optional( T&& _value ):
3550 nullableValue( new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( _value ) ) ) {}
3551
3552 Optional& operator=( T const& _value ) {
3553 reset();
3554 nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( _value );
3555 return *this;
3556 }
3557 Optional& operator=( T&& _value ) {
3558 reset();
3559 nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( _value ) );
3560 return *this;
3561 }
3562
3563 Optional( Optional const& _other ):
3564 nullableValue( _other ? new ( storage ) T( *_other ) : nullptr ) {}
3565 Optional( Optional&& _other ):
3566 nullableValue( _other ? new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( *_other ) )
3567 : nullptr ) {}
3568
3569 Optional& operator=( Optional const& _other ) {
3570 if ( &_other != this ) {
3571 reset();
3572 if ( _other ) { nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( *_other ); }
3573 }
3574 return *this;
3575 }
3576 Optional& operator=( Optional&& _other ) {
3577 if ( &_other != this ) {
3578 reset();
3579 if ( _other ) {
3580 nullableValue = new ( storage ) T( CATCH_MOVE( *_other ) );
3581 }
3582 }
3583 return *this;
3584 }
3585
3586 void reset() {
3587 if ( nullableValue ) { nullableValue->~T(); }
3588 nullableValue = nullptr;
3589 }
3590
3591 T& operator*() {
3592 assert(nullableValue);
3593 return *nullableValue;
3594 }
3595 T const& operator*() const {
3596 assert(nullableValue);
3597 return *nullableValue;
3598 }
3599 T* operator->() {
3600 assert(nullableValue);
3601 return nullableValue;
3602 }
3603 const T* operator->() const {
3604 assert(nullableValue);
3605 return nullableValue;
3606 }
3607
3608 T valueOr( T const& defaultValue ) const {
3609 return nullableValue ? *nullableValue : defaultValue;
3610 }
3611
3612 bool some() const { return nullableValue != nullptr; }
3613 bool none() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
3614
3615 bool operator !() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
3616 explicit operator bool() const {
3617 return some();
3618 }
3619
3620 friend bool operator==(Optional const& a, Optional const& b) {
3621 if (a.none() && b.none()) {
3622 return true;
3623 } else if (a.some() && b.some()) {
3624 return *a == *b;
3625 } else {
3626 return false;
3627 }
3628 }
3629 friend bool operator!=(Optional const& a, Optional const& b) {
3630 return !( a == b );
3631 }
3632
3633 private:
3634 T* nullableValue;
3635 alignas(alignof(T)) char storage[sizeof(T)];
3636 };
3637
3638} // end namespace Catch

3640#endif // CATCH_OPTIONAL_HPP_INCLUDED

3981 return sequence == other.sequence;
3982 }

3985 return sequence < other.sequence;
3986 }

4018 m_info(macroName, lineInfo, type) {}

4040 class Capturer {
4041 std::vector<MessageInfo> m_messages;
4042 size_t m_captured = 0;
4043 public:
4044 Capturer( StringRef macroName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, ResultWas::OfType resultType, StringRef names );
4045
4046 Capturer(Capturer const&) = delete;
4047 Capturer& operator=(Capturer const&) = delete;
4048
4049 ~Capturer();
4050
4051 void captureValue( size_t index, std::string const& value );
4052
4053 template<typename T>
4054 void captureValues( size_t index, T const& value ) {
4055 captureValue( index, Catch::Detail::stringify( value ) );
4056 }
4057
4058 template<typename T, typename... Ts>
4059 void captureValues( size_t index, T const& value, Ts const&... values ) {
4060 captureValue( index, Catch::Detail::stringify(value) );
4061 captureValues( index+1, values... );
4062 }
4063 };

4068#define INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( macroName, messageType, resultDisposition, ... ) \
4069 do { \
4070 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), resultDisposition ); \
4071 catchAssertionHandler.handleMessage( messageType, ( Catch::MessageStream() << __VA_ARGS__ + ::Catch::StreamEndStop() ).m_stream.str() ); \
4072 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
4073 } while( false )
4074
4076#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( varName, macroName, ... ) \
4077 Catch::Capturer varName( macroName##_catch_sr, \
4078 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
4079 Catch::ResultWas::Info, \
4080 #__VA_ARGS__##_catch_sr ); \
4081 varName.captureValues( 0, __VA_ARGS__ )
4082
4084#define INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( macroName, log ) \
4085 const Catch::ScopedMessage INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( scopedMessage )( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
4086
4088#define INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( macroName, log ) \
4089 Catch::IResultCapture::emplaceUnscopedMessage( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
4090
4091
4092#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_MESSAGES) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4093
4094 #define CATCH_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( "CATCH_INFO", msg )
4095 #define CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( "CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO", msg )
4096 #define CATCH_WARN( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "CATCH_WARN", Catch::ResultWas::Warning, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, msg )
4097 #define CATCH_CAPTURE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(capturer), "CATCH_CAPTURE", __VA_ARGS__ )
4098
4099#elif defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_MESSAGES) && defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4100
4101 #define CATCH_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4102 #define CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) (void)(0)
4103 #define CATCH_WARN( msg ) (void)(0)
4104 #define CATCH_CAPTURE( ... ) (void)(0)
4105
4106#elif !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_MESSAGES) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
4107
4108 #define INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( "INFO", msg )
4109 #define UNSCOPED_INFO( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( "UNSCOPED_INFO", msg )
4110 #define WARN( msg ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "WARN", Catch::ResultWas::Warning, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, msg )
4111 #define CAPTURE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(capturer), "CAPTURE", __VA_ARGS__ )

4258 struct fake_arg {
4259 template <typename T>
4260 operator T();
4261 };
4262
4263 template <typename F, typename = void>
4264 static constexpr bool is_unary_function_v = false;
4265
4266 template <typename F>
4267 static constexpr bool is_unary_function_v<
4268 F,
4269 Catch::Detail::void_t<decltype( std::declval<F>()(
4270 fake_arg() ) )>> = true;
4271
4272 // Traits for extracting arg and return type of lambdas (for single
4273 // argument lambdas)
4274 template <typename L>
4275 struct UnaryLambdaTraits
4276 : UnaryLambdaTraits<decltype( &L::operator() )> {};
4277
4278 template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename... Args>
4279 struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( Args... ) const> {
4280 static const bool isValid = false;
4281 };
4282
4283 template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename ArgT>
4284 struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( ArgT ) const> {
4285 static const bool isValid = true;
4286 using ArgType = std::remove_const_t<std::remove_reference_t<ArgT>>;
4287 using ReturnType = ReturnT;
4288 };
4289
4290 class TokenStream;
4291
4292 // Wraps a token coming from a token stream. These may not directly
4293 // correspond to strings as a single string may encode an option +
4294 // its argument if the : or = form is used
4295 enum class TokenType { Option, Argument };
4296 struct Token {
4297 TokenType type;
4298 StringRef token;
4299 };
4300
4301 // Abstracts iterators into args as a stream of tokens, with option
4302 // arguments uniformly handled
4303 class TokenStream {
4304 using Iterator = std::vector<StringRef>::const_iterator;
4305 Iterator it;
4306 Iterator itEnd;
4307 std::vector<Token> m_tokenBuffer;
4308 void loadBuffer();
4309
4310 public:
4311 explicit TokenStream( Args const& args );
4312 TokenStream( Iterator it, Iterator itEnd );
4313
4314 explicit operator bool() const {
4315 return !m_tokenBuffer.empty() || it != itEnd;
4316 }
4317
4318 size_t count() const {
4319 return m_tokenBuffer.size() + ( itEnd - it );
4320 }
4321
4322 Token operator*() const {
4323 assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4324 return m_tokenBuffer.front();
4325 }
4326
4327 Token const* operator->() const {
4328 assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4329 return &m_tokenBuffer.front();
4330 }
4331
4332 TokenStream& operator++();
4333 };
4334
4336 enum class ResultType {
4337 Ok,
4338 LogicError,
4340 RuntimeError
4341 };
4342
4343 class ResultBase {
4344 protected:
4345 ResultBase( ResultType type ): m_type( type ) {}
4346 virtual ~ResultBase(); // = default;
4347
4348
4349 ResultBase(ResultBase const&) = default;
4350 ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase const&) = default;
4351 ResultBase(ResultBase&&) = default;
4352 ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase&&) = default;
4353
4354 virtual void enforceOk() const = 0;
4355
4356 ResultType m_type;
4357 };
4358
4359 template <typename T>
4360 class ResultValueBase : public ResultBase {
4361 public:
4362 T const& value() const& {
4363 enforceOk();
4364 return m_value;
4365 }
4366 T&& value() && {
4367 enforceOk();
4368 return CATCH_MOVE( m_value );
4369 }
4370
4371 protected:
4372 ResultValueBase( ResultType type ): ResultBase( type ) {}
4373
4374 ResultValueBase( ResultValueBase const& other ):
4375 ResultBase( other ) {
4376 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4377 new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4378 }
4379 ResultValueBase( ResultValueBase&& other ):
4380 ResultBase( other ) {
4381 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4382 new ( &m_value ) T( CATCH_MOVE(other.m_value) );
4383 }
4384
4385
4386 ResultValueBase( ResultType, T const& value ):
4387 ResultBase( ResultType::Ok ) {
4388 new ( &m_value ) T( value );
4389 }
4390 ResultValueBase( ResultType, T&& value ):
4391 ResultBase( ResultType::Ok ) {
4392 new ( &m_value ) T( CATCH_MOVE(value) );
4393 }
4394
4395 ResultValueBase& operator=( ResultValueBase const& other ) {
4396 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4397 m_value.~T();
4398 ResultBase::operator=( other );
4399 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4400 new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4401 return *this;
4402 }
4403 ResultValueBase& operator=( ResultValueBase&& other ) {
4404 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok ) m_value.~T();
4405 ResultBase::operator=( other );
4406 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4407 new ( &m_value ) T( CATCH_MOVE(other.m_value) );
4408 return *this;
4409 }
4410
4411
4412 ~ResultValueBase() override {
4413 if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4414 m_value.~T();
4415 }
4416
4417 union {
4418 T m_value;
4419 };
4420 };
4421
4422 template <> class ResultValueBase<void> : public ResultBase {
4423 protected:
4424 using ResultBase::ResultBase;
4425 };
4426
4427 template <typename T = void>
4428 class BasicResult : public ResultValueBase<T> {
4429 public:
4430 template <typename U>
4431 explicit BasicResult( BasicResult<U> const& other ):
4432 ResultValueBase<T>( other.type() ),
4433 m_errorMessage( other.errorMessage() ) {
4434 assert( type() != ResultType::Ok );
4435 }
4436
4437 template <typename U>
4438 static auto ok( U&& value ) -> BasicResult {
4439 return { ResultType::Ok, CATCH_FORWARD(value) };
4440 }
4441 static auto ok() -> BasicResult { return { ResultType::Ok }; }
4442 static auto logicError( std::string&& message )
4443 -> BasicResult {
4444 return { ResultType::LogicError, CATCH_MOVE(message) };
4445 }
4446 static auto runtimeError( std::string&& message )
4447 -> BasicResult {
4448 return { ResultType::RuntimeError, CATCH_MOVE(message) };
4449 }
4450
4451 explicit operator bool() const {
4452 return m_type == ResultType::Ok;
4453 }
4454 auto type() const -> ResultType { return m_type; }
4455 auto errorMessage() const -> std::string const& {
4456 return m_errorMessage;
4457 }
4458
4459 protected:
4460 void enforceOk() const override {
4461
4462 // Errors shouldn't reach this point, but if they do
4463 // the actual error message will be in m_errorMessage
4464 assert( m_type != ResultType::LogicError );
4465 assert( m_type != ResultType::RuntimeError );
4466 if ( m_type != ResultType::Ok )
4467 std::abort();
4468 }
4469
4470 std::string
4471 m_errorMessage; // Only populated if resultType is an error
4472
4473 BasicResult( ResultType type,
4474 std::string&& message ):
4475 ResultValueBase<T>( type ), m_errorMessage( CATCH_MOVE(message) ) {
4476 assert( m_type != ResultType::Ok );
4477 }
4478
4479 using ResultValueBase<T>::ResultValueBase;
4480 using ResultBase::m_type;
4481 };
4482
4483 class ParseState {
4484 public:
4485 ParseState( ParseResultType type,
4486 TokenStream remainingTokens );
4487
4488 ParseResultType type() const { return m_type; }
4489 TokenStream const& remainingTokens() const& {
4490 return m_remainingTokens;
4491 }
4492 TokenStream&& remainingTokens() && {
4493 return CATCH_MOVE( m_remainingTokens );
4494 }
4495
4496 private:
4497 ParseResultType m_type;
4498 TokenStream m_remainingTokens;
4499 };
4500
4501 using Result = BasicResult<void>;
4502 using ParserResult = BasicResult<ParseResultType>;
4503 using InternalParseResult = BasicResult<ParseState>;
4504
4505 struct HelpColumns {
4506 std::string left;
4507 StringRef descriptions;
4508 };
4509
4510 template <typename T>
4511 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, T& target ) {
4512 std::stringstream ss( source );
4513 ss >> target;
4514 if ( ss.fail() ) {
4515 return ParserResult::runtimeError(
4516 "Unable to convert '" + source +
4517 "' to destination type" );
4518 } else {
4519 return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4520 }
4521 }
4522 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source,
4523 std::string& target );
4524 ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, bool& target );
4525
4526#ifdef CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4527 template <typename T>
4528 auto convertInto( std::string const& source,
4529 CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE<T>& target )
4530 -> ParserResult {
4531 T temp;
4532 auto result = convertInto( source, temp );
4533 if ( result )
4534 target = CATCH_MOVE( temp );
4535 return result;
4536 }
4537#endif // CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4538
4539 struct BoundRef : Catch::Detail::NonCopyable {
4540 virtual ~BoundRef() = default;
4541 virtual bool isContainer() const;
4542 virtual bool isFlag() const;
4543 };
4544 struct BoundValueRefBase : BoundRef {
4545 virtual auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4546 -> ParserResult = 0;
4547 };
4548 struct BoundFlagRefBase : BoundRef {
4549 virtual auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult = 0;
4550 bool isFlag() const override;
4551 };
4552
4553 template <typename T> struct BoundValueRef : BoundValueRefBase {
4554 T& m_ref;
4555
4556 explicit BoundValueRef( T& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4557
4558 ParserResult setValue( std::string const& arg ) override {
4559 return convertInto( arg, m_ref );
4560 }
4561 };
4562
4563 template <typename T>
4564 struct BoundValueRef<std::vector<T>> : BoundValueRefBase {
4565 std::vector<T>& m_ref;
4566
4567 explicit BoundValueRef( std::vector<T>& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4568
4569 auto isContainer() const -> bool override { return true; }
4570
4571 auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4572 -> ParserResult override {
4573 T temp;
4574 auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4575 if ( result )
4576 m_ref.push_back( temp );
4577 return result;
4578 }
4579 };
4580
4581 struct BoundFlagRef : BoundFlagRefBase {
4582 bool& m_ref;
4583
4584 explicit BoundFlagRef( bool& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4585
4586 ParserResult setFlag( bool flag ) override;
4587 };
4588
4589 template <typename ReturnType> struct LambdaInvoker {
4590 static_assert(
4591 std::is_same<ReturnType, ParserResult>::value,
4592 "Lambda must return void or clara::ParserResult" );
4593
4594 template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4595 static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4596 -> ParserResult {
4597 return lambda( arg );
4598 }
4599 };
4600
4601 template <> struct LambdaInvoker<void> {
4602 template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4603 static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4604 -> ParserResult {
4605 lambda( arg );
4606 return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4607 }
4608 };
4609
4610 template <typename ArgType, typename L>
4611 auto invokeLambda( L const& lambda, std::string const& arg )
4612 -> ParserResult {
4613 ArgType temp{};
4614 auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4615 return !result ? result
4616 : LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4617 L>::ReturnType>::invoke( lambda, temp );
4618 }
4619
4620 template <typename L> struct BoundLambda : BoundValueRefBase {
4621 L m_lambda;
4622
4623 static_assert(
4624 UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4625 "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4626 explicit BoundLambda( L const& lambda ): m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4627
4628 auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4629 -> ParserResult override {
4630 return invokeLambda<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType>(
4631 m_lambda, arg );
4632 }
4633 };
4634
4635 template <typename L> struct BoundManyLambda : BoundLambda<L> {
4636 explicit BoundManyLambda( L const& lambda ): BoundLambda<L>( lambda ) {}
4637 bool isContainer() const override { return true; }
4638 };
4639
4640 template <typename L> struct BoundFlagLambda : BoundFlagRefBase {
4641 L m_lambda;
4642
4643 static_assert(
4644 UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4645 "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4646 static_assert(
4647 std::is_same<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType,
4648 bool>::value,
4649 "flags must be boolean" );
4650
4651 explicit BoundFlagLambda( L const& lambda ):
4652 m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4653
4654 auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult override {
4655 return LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4656 L>::ReturnType>::invoke( m_lambda, flag );
4657 }
4658 };
4659
4660 enum class Optionality { Optional, Required };
4661
4662 class ParserBase {
4663 public:
4664 virtual ~ParserBase() = default;
4665 virtual auto validate() const -> Result { return Result::ok(); }
4666 virtual auto parse( std::string const& exeName,
4667 TokenStream tokens ) const
4668 -> InternalParseResult = 0;
4669 virtual size_t cardinality() const;
4670
4671 InternalParseResult parse( Args const& args ) const;
4672 };
4673
4674 template <typename DerivedT>
4675 class ComposableParserImpl : public ParserBase {
4676 public:
4677 template <typename T>
4678 auto operator|( T const& other ) const -> Parser;
4679 };
4680
4681 // Common code and state for Args and Opts
4682 template <typename DerivedT>
4683 class ParserRefImpl : public ComposableParserImpl<DerivedT> {
4684 protected:
4685 Optionality m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
4686 std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> m_ref;
4687 StringRef m_hint;
4688 StringRef m_description;
4689
4690 explicit ParserRefImpl( std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> const& ref ):
4691 m_ref( ref ) {}
4692
4693 public:
4694 template <typename LambdaT>
4695 ParserRefImpl( accept_many_t,
4696 LambdaT const& ref,
4697 StringRef hint ):
4698 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundManyLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
4699 m_hint( hint ) {}
4700
4701 template <typename T,
4702 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
4703 !Detail::is_unary_function_v<T>>>
4704 ParserRefImpl( T& ref, StringRef hint ):
4705 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundValueRef<T>>( ref ) ),
4706 m_hint( hint ) {}
4707
4708 template <typename LambdaT,
4709 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
4710 Detail::is_unary_function_v<LambdaT>>>
4711 ParserRefImpl( LambdaT const& ref, StringRef hint ):
4712 m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
4713 m_hint( hint ) {}
4714
4715 DerivedT& operator()( StringRef description ) & {
4716 m_description = description;
4717 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4718 }
4719 DerivedT&& operator()( StringRef description ) && {
4720 m_description = description;
4721 return static_cast<DerivedT&&>( *this );
4722 }
4723
4724 auto optional() -> DerivedT& {
4725 m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
4726 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4727 }
4728
4729 auto required() -> DerivedT& {
4730 m_optionality = Optionality::Required;
4731 return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4732 }
4733
4734 auto isOptional() const -> bool {
4735 return m_optionality == Optionality::Optional;
4736 }
4737
4738 auto cardinality() const -> size_t override {
4739 if ( m_ref->isContainer() )
4740 return 0;
4741 else
4742 return 1;
4743 }
4744
4745 StringRef hint() const { return m_hint; }
4746 };
4747
4748 } // namespace detail

4838 // A Combined parser
4839 class Parser : Detail::ParserBase {
4840 mutable ExeName m_exeName;
4841 std::vector<Opt> m_options;
4842 std::vector<Arg> m_args;
4843
4844 public:
4845
4846 auto operator|=(ExeName const& exeName) -> Parser& {
4847 m_exeName = exeName;
4848 return *this;
4849 }
4850
4851 auto operator|=(Arg const& arg) -> Parser& {
4852 m_args.push_back(arg);
4853 return *this;
4854 }
4855
4856 friend Parser& operator|=( Parser& p, Opt const& opt ) {
4857 p.m_options.push_back( opt );
4858 return p;
4859 }
4860 friend Parser& operator|=( Parser& p, Opt&& opt ) {
4861 p.m_options.push_back( CATCH_MOVE(opt) );
4862 return p;
4863 }
4864
4865 Parser& operator|=(Parser const& other);
4866
4867 template <typename T>
4868 friend Parser operator|( Parser const& p, T&& rhs ) {
4869 Parser temp( p );
4870 temp |= rhs;
4871 return temp;
4872 }
4873
4874 template <typename T>
4875 friend Parser operator|( Parser&& p, T&& rhs ) {
4876 p |= CATCH_FORWARD(rhs);
4877 return CATCH_MOVE(p);
4878 }
4879
4880 std::vector<Detail::HelpColumns> getHelpColumns() const;
4881
4882 void writeToStream(std::ostream& os) const;
4883
4884 friend auto operator<<(std::ostream& os, Parser const& parser)
4885 -> std::ostream& {
4886 parser.writeToStream(os);
4887 return os;
4888 }
4889
4890 Detail::Result validate() const override;
4891
4892 using ParserBase::parse;
4893 Detail::InternalParseResult
4894 parse(std::string const& exeName,
4895 Detail::TokenStream tokens) const override;
4896 };

4929 }

5089#ifndef CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED
5090#define CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED
5091
5092
5093#include <type_traits>
5094
5095namespace Catch {
5096 namespace Detail {
5097
5098#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && !defined( __clang__ )
5099# pragma GCC diagnostic push
5100 // GCC likes to complain about comparing bool with 0, in the decltype()
5101 // that defines the comparable traits below.
5102# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wbool-compare"
5103 // "ordered comparison of pointer with integer zero" same as above,
5104 // but it does not have a separate warning flag to suppress
5105# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wextra"
5106 // Did you know that comparing floats with `0` directly
5107 // is super-duper dangerous in unevaluated context?
5108# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
5109#endif
5110
5111#if defined( __clang__ )
5112# pragma clang diagnostic push
5113 // Did you know that comparing floats with `0` directly
5114 // is super-duper dangerous in unevaluated context?
5115# pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
5116#endif
5117
5118#define CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( id, op ) \
5119 template <typename, typename, typename = void> \
5120 struct is_##id##_comparable : std::false_type {}; \
5121 template <typename T, typename U> \
5122 struct is_##id##_comparable< \
5123 T, \
5124 U, \
5125 void_t<decltype( std::declval<T>() op std::declval<U>() )>> \
5126 : std::true_type {}; \
5127 template <typename, typename = void> \
5128 struct is_##id##_0_comparable : std::false_type {}; \
5129 template <typename T> \
5130 struct is_##id##_0_comparable<T, \
5131 void_t<decltype( std::declval<T>() op 0 )>> \
5132 : std::true_type {};
5133
5134 // We need all 6 pre-spaceship comparison ops: <, <=, >, >=, ==, !=
5135 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( lt, < )
5136 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( le, <= )
5137 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( gt, > )
5138 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( ge, >= )
5139 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( eq, == )
5140 CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT( ne, != )
5141
5142#undef CATCH_DEFINE_COMPARABLE_TRAIT
5143
5144#if defined( __GNUC__ ) && !defined( __clang__ )
5145# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
5146#endif
5147#if defined( __clang__ )
5148# pragma clang diagnostic pop
5149#endif
5150
5151
5152 } // namespace Detail
5153} // namespace Catch

5155#endif // CATCH_COMPARE_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED

5166#if defined( __cpp_lib_logical_traits ) && __cpp_lib_logical_traits >= 201510

5168 using std::conjunction;
5169 using std::disjunction;
5170 using std::negation;
5171
5172#else
5173
5174 template <class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
5175 template <class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
5176 template <class B1, class... Bn>
5177 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...>
5178 : std::conditional_t<bool( B1::value ), conjunction<Bn...>, B1> {};
5179
5180 template <class...> struct disjunction : std::false_type {};
5181 template <class B1> struct disjunction<B1> : B1 {};
5182 template <class B1, class... Bn>
5183 struct disjunction<B1, Bn...>
5184 : std::conditional_t<bool( B1::value ), B1, disjunction<Bn...>> {};
5185
5186 template <class B>
5187 struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, !bool(B::value)> {};
5188
5189#endif
5190
5191} // namespace Detail
5192} // namespace Catch
5193
5194#endif // CATCH_LOGICAL_TRAITS_HPP_INCLUDED

5310 // This was added in C++20, but we require only C++14 for now.
5311 template <typename T>
5312 using RemoveCVRef_t = std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>;
5313 }
5314
5315 // Note: This is about as much as we can currently reasonably support.
5316 // In an ideal world, we could capture by value small trivially
5317 // copyable types, but the actual `std::is_trivially_copyable`
5318 // trait is a huge mess with standard-violating results on
5319 // GCC and Clang, which are unlikely to be fixed soon due to ABI
5320 // concerns.
5321 // `std::is_scalar` also causes issues due to the `is_pointer`
5322 // component, which causes ambiguity issues with (references-to)
5323 // function pointer. If those are resolved, we still need to
5324 // disambiguate the overload set for arrays, through explicit
5325 // overload for references to sized arrays.
5326 template <typename T>
5327 struct capture_by_value
5328 : std::integral_constant<bool,
5329 std::is_arithmetic<T>::value ||
5330 std::is_enum<T>::value> {};
5331
5332#if defined( CATCH_CONFIG_CPP20_COMPARE_OVERLOADS )
5333 template <>
5334 struct capture_by_value<std::strong_ordering> : std::true_type {};
5335 template <>
5336 struct capture_by_value<std::weak_ordering> : std::true_type {};
5337 template <>
5338 struct capture_by_value<std::partial_ordering> : std::true_type {};
5339#endif

5341 template <typename T>
5342 struct always_false : std::false_type {};
