5344 class ITransientExpression {
5345 bool m_isBinaryExpression;
5346 bool m_result;
5347
5348 protected:
5349 ~ITransientExpression() = default;
5350
5351 public:
5352 constexpr auto isBinaryExpression() const -> bool { return m_isBinaryExpression; }
5353 constexpr auto getResult() const -> bool { return m_result; }
5355 virtual void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream& os ) const;
5356
5357 constexpr ITransientExpression( bool isBinaryExpression, bool result )
5358 : m_isBinaryExpression( isBinaryExpression ),
5359 m_result( result )
5360 {}
5361
5362 constexpr ITransientExpression( ITransientExpression const& ) = default;
5363 constexpr ITransientExpression& operator=( ITransientExpression const& ) = default;
5364
5365 friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& out, ITransientExpression const& expr) {
5366 expr.streamReconstructedExpression(out);
5367 return out;
5368 }
5369 };
5370
5371 void formatReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os, std::string const& lhs, StringRef op, std::string const& rhs );
5372
5373 template<typename LhsT, typename RhsT>
5374 class BinaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
5375 LhsT m_lhs;
5376 StringRef m_op;
5377 RhsT m_rhs;
5378
5379 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
5380 formatReconstructedExpression
5381 ( os, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs ), m_op, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_rhs ) );
5382 }
5383
5384 public:
5385 constexpr BinaryExpr( bool comparisonResult, LhsT lhs, StringRef op, RhsT rhs )
5386 : ITransientExpression{ true, comparisonResult },
5387 m_lhs( lhs ),
5388 m_op( op ),
5389 m_rhs( rhs )
5390 {}
5391
5392 template<typename T>
5393 auto operator && ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5394 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5395 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5396 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5397 }
5398
5399 template<typename T>
5400 auto operator || ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5401 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5402 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5403 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5404 }
5405
5406 template<typename T>
5407 auto operator == ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5408 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5409 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5410 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5411 }
5412
5413 template<typename T>
5414 auto operator != ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5415 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5416 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5417 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5418 }
5419
5420 template<typename T>
5421 auto operator > ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5422 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5423 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5424 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5425 }
5426
5427 template<typename T>
5428 auto operator < ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5429 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5430 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5431 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5432 }
5433
5434 template<typename T>
5435 auto operator >= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5436 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5437 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5438 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5439 }
5440
5441 template<typename T>
5442 auto operator <= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5443 static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
5444 "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
5445 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5446 }
5447 };

5454 os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs );
5455 }

5459 : ITransientExpression{ false, static_cast<bool>(lhs) },
5460 m_lhs( lhs )

5465 template<typename LhsT>
5466 class ExprLhs {
5467 LhsT m_lhs;
5468 public:
5469 explicit constexpr ExprLhs( LhsT lhs ) : m_lhs( lhs ) {}
5470
5471#define CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( id, op ) \
5472 template <typename RhsT> \
5473 constexpr friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5474 -> std::enable_if_t< \
5475 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5476 Detail::negation<capture_by_value< \
5477 Detail::RemoveCVRef_t<RhsT>>>>::value, \
5478 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5479 return { \
5480 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5481 } \
5482 template <typename RhsT> \
5483 constexpr friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5484 -> std::enable_if_t< \
5485 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5486 capture_by_value<RhsT>>::value, \
5487 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5488 return { \
5489 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5490 } \
5491 template <typename RhsT> \
5492 constexpr friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5493 -> std::enable_if_t< \
5494 Detail::conjunction< \
5495 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5496 Detail::is_eq_0_comparable<LhsT>, \
5497 /* We allow long because we want `ptr op NULL` to be accepted */ \
5498 Detail::disjunction<std::is_same<RhsT, int>, \
5499 std::is_same<RhsT, long>>>::value, \
5500 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5501 if ( rhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5502 return { \
5503 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op 0 ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5504 } \
5505 template <typename RhsT> \
5506 constexpr friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5507 -> std::enable_if_t< \
5508 Detail::conjunction< \
5509 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5510 Detail::is_eq_0_comparable<RhsT>, \
5511 /* We allow long because we want `ptr op NULL` to be accepted */ \
5512 Detail::disjunction<std::is_same<LhsT, int>, \
5513 std::is_same<LhsT, long>>>::value, \
5514 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5515 if ( lhs.m_lhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5516 return { static_cast<bool>( 0 op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5517 }
5518
5519 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( eq, == )
5520 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_EQUALITY_OPERATOR( ne, != )
5521

5528 -> std::enable_if_t< \
5529 Detail::conjunction<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>, \
5530 Detail::negation<capture_by_value< \

5533 return { \
5534 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5535 } \

5538 -> std::enable_if_t< \

5540 capture_by_value<RhsT>>::value, \
5541 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5542 return { \
5543 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5544 } \

5553 if ( rhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5554 return { \
5555 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op 0 ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5556 } \

5560 Detail::conjunction< \
5561 Detail::negation<Detail::is_##id##_comparable<LhsT, RhsT>>, \
5562 Detail::is_##id##_0_comparable<RhsT>, \
5563 std::is_same<LhsT, int>>::value, \
5564 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5565 if ( lhs.m_lhs != 0 ) { throw_test_failure_exception(); } \
5566 return { static_cast<bool>( 0 op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5567 }

5569 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( lt, < )
5570 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( le, <= )
5571 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_COMPARISON_OPERATOR( gt, > )

5578 template <typename RhsT> \
5579 constexpr friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) \
5580 -> std::enable_if_t< \
5581 !capture_by_value<Detail::RemoveCVRef_t<RhsT>>::value, \
5582 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&>> { \
5583 return { \
5584 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5585 } \

5587 constexpr friend auto operator op( ExprLhs&& lhs, RhsT rhs ) \
5588 -> std::enable_if_t<capture_by_value<RhsT>::value, \
5589 BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT>> { \
5590 return { \
5591 static_cast<bool>( lhs.m_lhs op rhs ), lhs.m_lhs, #op##_sr, rhs }; \
5592 }

5594 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(|)
5595 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(&)
5596 CATCH_INTERNAL_DEFINE_EXPRESSION_OPERATOR(^)

5600 template<typename RhsT>
5601 friend auto operator && ( ExprLhs &&, RhsT && ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> {
5602 static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5603 "operator&& is not supported inside assertions, "
5604 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5605 }
5606
5607 template<typename RhsT>
5608 friend auto operator || ( ExprLhs &&, RhsT && ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> {
5609 static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5610 "operator|| is not supported inside assertions, "
5611 "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5612 }
5613
5614 constexpr auto makeUnaryExpr() const -> UnaryExpr<LhsT> {
5615 return UnaryExpr<LhsT>{ m_lhs };
5616 }
5617 };

5619 struct Decomposer {
5620 template <typename T,
5621 std::enable_if_t<!capture_by_value<Detail::RemoveCVRef_t<T>>::value,
5622 int> = 0>
5623 constexpr friend auto operator <= ( Decomposer &&, T && lhs ) -> ExprLhs<T const&> {
5624 return ExprLhs<const T&>{ lhs };
5625 }
5626
5627 template <typename T,
5628 std::enable_if_t<capture_by_value<T>::value, int> = 0>
5629 constexpr friend auto operator <= ( Decomposer &&, T value ) -> ExprLhs<T> {
5630 return ExprLhs<T>{ value };
5631 }
5632 };

5651 struct AssertionReaction {
5652 bool shouldDebugBreak = false;
5653 bool shouldThrow = false;
5654 bool shouldSkip = false;

5657 class AssertionHandler {
5658 AssertionInfo m_assertionInfo;
5659 AssertionReaction m_reaction;
5660 bool m_completed = false;
5661 IResultCapture& m_resultCapture;
5662
5663 public:
5664 AssertionHandler
5665 ( StringRef macroName,
5666 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo,
5667 StringRef capturedExpression,
5668 ResultDisposition::Flags resultDisposition );
5669 ~AssertionHandler() {
5670 if ( !m_completed ) {
5671 m_resultCapture.handleIncomplete( m_assertionInfo );
5672 }
5673 }

5678 handleExpr( expr.makeUnaryExpr() );

5684 void handleExceptionThrownAsExpected();
5685 void handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown();
5686 void handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected();
5687 void handleThrowingCallSkipped();
5688 void handleUnexpectedInflightException();
5689
5690 void complete();
5691
5692 // query
5693 auto allowThrows() const -> bool;
5694 };

5709#else
5710 #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) "Disabled by CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION"_catch_sr

5716// for the front end to handle local suppression via _Pragma properly

5724
5726// Another way to speed-up compilation is to omit local try-catch for REQUIRE*
5727// macros.
5728#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY
5729#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( capturer )
5730
5731#else // CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE
5732
5733#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY try
5734#define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( handler ) catch(...) { (handler).handleUnexpectedInflightException(); }
5735
5736#endif
5737
5739#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5740 do { /* NOLINT(bugprone-infinite-loop) */ \
5741 /* The expression should not be evaluated, but warnings should hopefully be checked */ \
5742 CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(__VA_ARGS__); \
5743 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5744 INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
5745 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5746 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
5747 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::Decomposer() <= __VA_ARGS__ ); /* NOLINT(bugprone-chained-comparison) */ \
5748 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5749 } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5750 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
5751 } while( (void)0, (false) && static_cast<const bool&>( !!(__VA_ARGS__) ) ) // the expression here is never evaluated at runtime but it forces the compiler to give it a look
5752 // The double negation silences MSVC's C4800 warning, the static_cast forces short-circuit evaluation if the type has overloaded &&.
5753
5755#define INTERNAL_CATCH_IF( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5756 INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5757 if( Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5758
5760#define INTERNAL_CATCH_ELSE( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5761 INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5762 if( !Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5763
5765#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5766 do { \
5767 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5768 try { \
5769 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5770 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5771 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5772 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5773 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected(); \
5774 } \
5775 catch( ... ) { \
5776 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5777 } \
5778 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
5779 } while( false )
5780
5782#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5783 do { \
5784 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition); \
5785 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5786 try { \
5787 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5788 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_RESULT \
5789 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5790 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5791 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5792 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5793 } \
5794 catch( ... ) { \
5795 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5796 } \
5797 else \
5798 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5799 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
5800 } while( false )
5801
5803#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_AS( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, expr ) \
5804 do { \
5805 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(expr) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType), resultDisposition ); \
5806 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5807 try { \
5808 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5809 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_RESULT \
5810 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5811 static_cast<void>(expr); \
5812 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5813 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5814 } \
5815 catch( exceptionType const& ) { \
5816 catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5817 } \
5818 catch( ... ) { \
5819 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5820 } \
5821 else \
5822 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5823 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
5824 } while( false )

5827
5829// Although this is matcher-based, it can be used with just a string
5830#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_STR_MATCHES( macroName, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
5831 do { \
5832 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
5833 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5834 try { \
5835 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5836 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_RESULT \
5837 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
5838 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5839 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5840 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5841 } \
5842 catch( ... ) { \
5843 Catch::handleExceptionMatchExpr( catchAssertionHandler, matcher ); \
5844 } \
5845 else \
5846 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5847 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
5848 } while( false )
5849
5850#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE
5851
5852#endif // CATCH_TEST_MACRO_IMPL_HPP_INCLUDED

5954// These section definitions imply that at most one section at one level
5955// will be entered (because only one section's __LINE__ can be equal to
5956// the dummy `catchInternalSectionHint` variable from `TEST_CASE`).
5957
5958namespace Catch {
5959 namespace Detail {
5960 // Intentionally without linkage, as it should only be used as a dummy
5961 // symbol for static analysis.
5962 // The arguments are used as a dummy for checking warnings in the passed
5963 // expressions.
5964 int GetNewSectionHint( StringRef, const char* const = nullptr );
5965 } // namespace Detail
5966} // namespace Catch
5967
5968
5969# define INTERNAL_CATCH_SECTION( ... ) \
5970 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5971 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
5972 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_SHADOW_WARNINGS \
5973 if ( [[maybe_unused]] const int catchInternalPreviousSectionHint = \
5974 catchInternalSectionHint, \
5975 catchInternalSectionHint = \
5976 Catch::Detail::GetNewSectionHint(__VA_ARGS__); \
5977 catchInternalPreviousSectionHint == __LINE__ ) \
5978 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
5979
5980# define INTERNAL_CATCH_DYNAMIC_SECTION( ... ) \
5981 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5982 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
5983 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_SHADOW_WARNINGS \
5984 if ( [[maybe_unused]] const int catchInternalPreviousSectionHint = \
5985 catchInternalSectionHint, \
5986 catchInternalSectionHint = Catch::Detail::GetNewSectionHint( \
5987 ( Catch::ReusableStringStream() << __VA_ARGS__ ).str()); \
5988 catchInternalPreviousSectionHint == __LINE__ ) \
5989 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
5990
5991#endif

6033// GCC 5 and older do not properly handle disabling unused-variable warning
6034// with a _Pragma. This means that we have to leak the suppression to the

6042namespace Catch {
6043
6044template<typename C>
6045class TestInvokerAsMethod : public ITestInvoker {
6046 void (C::*m_testAsMethod)();
6047public:
6048 constexpr TestInvokerAsMethod( void ( C::*testAsMethod )() ) noexcept:
6049 m_testAsMethod( testAsMethod ) {}
6050
6051 void invoke() const override {
6052 C obj;
6053 (obj.*m_testAsMethod)();
6054 }
6055};
6056
6057Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void(*testAsFunction)() );
6058
6059template<typename C>
6060Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) {
6061 return Detail::make_unique<TestInvokerAsMethod<C>>( testAsMethod );
6062}
6063
6064template <typename C>
6065class TestInvokerFixture : public ITestInvoker {
6066 void ( C::*m_testAsMethod )() const;
6067 Detail::unique_ptr<C> m_fixture = nullptr;
6068
6069public:
6070 constexpr TestInvokerFixture( void ( C::*testAsMethod )() const ) noexcept:
6071 m_testAsMethod( testAsMethod ) {}
6072
6073 void prepareTestCase() override {
6074 m_fixture = Detail::make_unique<C>();
6075 }
6076
6077 void tearDownTestCase() override {
6078 m_fixture.reset();
6079 }
6080
6081 void invoke() const override {
6082 auto* f = m_fixture.get();
6083 ( f->*m_testAsMethod )();
6084 }
6085};
6086
6087template<typename C>
6088Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvokerFixture( void ( C::*testAsMethod )() const ) {
6089 return Detail::make_unique<TestInvokerFixture<C>>( testAsMethod );
6090}
6091
6092struct NameAndTags {
6093 constexpr NameAndTags( StringRef name_ = StringRef(),
6094 StringRef tags_ = StringRef() ) noexcept:
6095 name( name_ ), tags( tags_ ) {}
6096 StringRef name;
6097 StringRef tags;
6098};

6100struct AutoReg : Detail::NonCopyable {
6101 AutoReg( Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> invoker, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, StringRef classOrMethod, NameAndTags const& nameAndTags ) noexcept;
6102};

6260#else // vv If we do not have std::unreachable, we implement something similar

6262namespace Catch {

6264
6265 [[noreturn]]
6266 inline void Unreachable() noexcept {
6267# if defined( NDEBUG )
6268# if defined( _MSC_VER ) && !defined( __clang__ )
6269 __assume( false );
6270# elif defined( __GNUC__ )
6271 __builtin_unreachable();
6272# else // vv platform without known optimization hint
6273 std::terminate();
6274# endif
6275# else // ^^ NDEBUG
6276 // For non-release builds, we prefer termination on bug over UB
6277 std::terminate();
6278# endif //
6279 }

6281 } // namespace Detail
6282} // end namespace Catch

6289// All of our user-facing macros support configuration toggle, that
6290// forces them to be defined prefixed with CATCH_. We also like to
6291// support another toggle that can minimize (disable) their implementation.
6292// Given this, we have 4 different configuration options below
6293
6294#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
6295
6296 #define CATCH_REQUIRE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_REQUIRE", Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, __VA_ARGS__ )
6297 #define CATCH_REQUIRE_FALSE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_REQUIRE_FALSE", Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal | Catch::ResultDisposition::FalseTest, __VA_ARGS__ )
6298
6299 #define CATCH_REQUIRE_THROWS( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS( "CATCH_REQUIRE_THROWS", Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, __VA_ARGS__ )
6300 #define CATCH_REQUIRE_THROWS_AS( expr, exceptionType ) INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_AS( "CATCH_REQUIRE_THROWS_AS", exceptionType, Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, expr )
6301 #define CATCH_REQUIRE_NOTHROW( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( "CATCH_REQUIRE_NOTHROW", Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, __VA_ARGS__ )
6302
6303 #define CATCH_CHECK( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_CHECK", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, __VA_ARGS__ )
6304 #define CATCH_CHECK_FALSE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_CHECK_FALSE", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::FalseTest, __VA_ARGS__ )
6305 #define CATCH_CHECKED_IF( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_IF( "CATCH_CHECKED_IF", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::SuppressFail, __VA_ARGS__ )
6306 #define CATCH_CHECKED_ELSE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_ELSE( "CATCH_CHECKED_ELSE", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::SuppressFail, __VA_ARGS__ )
6307 #define CATCH_CHECK_NOFAIL( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( "CATCH_CHECK_NOFAIL", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure | Catch::ResultDisposition::SuppressFail, __VA_ARGS__ )
6308
6309 #define CATCH_CHECK_THROWS( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS( "CATCH_CHECK_THROWS", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, __VA_ARGS__ )
6310 #define CATCH_CHECK_THROWS_AS( expr, exceptionType ) INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_AS( "CATCH_CHECK_THROWS_AS", exceptionType, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, expr )
6311 #define CATCH_CHECK_NOTHROW( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( "CATCH_CHECK_NOTHROW", Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, __VA_ARGS__ )
6312
6313 #define CATCH_TEST_CASE( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TESTCASE( __VA_ARGS__ )
6314 #define CATCH_TEST_CASE_METHOD( className, ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST_CASE_METHOD( className, __VA_ARGS__ )
6315 #define CATCH_METHOD_AS_TEST_CASE( method, ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_METHOD_AS_TEST_CASE( method, __VA_ARGS__ )
6316 #define CATCH_TEST_CASE_PERSISTENT_FIXTURE( className, ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST_CASE_PERSISTENT_FIXTURE( className, __VA_ARGS__ )
6317 #define CATCH_REGISTER_TEST_CASE( Function, ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_REGISTER_TESTCASE( Function, __VA_ARGS__ )
6318 #define CATCH_SECTION( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_SECTION( __VA_ARGS__ )
6319 #define CATCH_DYNAMIC_SECTION( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_DYNAMIC_SECTION( __VA_ARGS__ )
6320 #define CATCH_FAIL( ... ) do { \
6321 INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG("CATCH_FAIL", Catch::ResultWas::ExplicitFailure, Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
6322 Catch::Detail::Unreachable(); \
6323 } while ( false )
6324 #define CATCH_FAIL_CHECK( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "CATCH_FAIL_CHECK", Catch::ResultWas::ExplicitFailure, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, __VA_ARGS__ )
6325 #define CATCH_SUCCEED( ... ) INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "CATCH_SUCCEED", Catch::ResultWas::Ok, Catch::ResultDisposition::ContinueOnFailure, __VA_ARGS__ )
6326 #define CATCH_SKIP( ... ) do { \
6327 INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( "CATCH_SKIP", Catch::ResultWas::ExplicitSkip, Catch::ResultDisposition::Normal, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
6328 Catch::Detail::Unreachable(); \
6329 } while (false)

6555#define CATCH_REC_END(...)
6556#define CATCH_REC_OUT
6557
6558#define CATCH_EMPTY()
6559#define CATCH_DEFER(id) id CATCH_EMPTY()
6560
6561#define CATCH_REC_GET_END2() 0, CATCH_REC_END
6562#define CATCH_REC_GET_END1(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END2
6563#define CATCH_REC_GET_END(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END1
6564#define CATCH_REC_NEXT0(test, next, ...) next CATCH_REC_OUT
6565#define CATCH_REC_NEXT1(test, next) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT0 ) ( test, next, 0)
6566#define CATCH_REC_NEXT(test, next) CATCH_REC_NEXT1(CATCH_REC_GET_END test, next)
6567
6568#define CATCH_REC_LIST0(f, x, peek, ...) , f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6569#define CATCH_REC_LIST1(f, x, peek, ...) , f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6570#define CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, x, peek, ...) f(x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1) ) ( f, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6571
6572#define CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6573#define CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6574#define CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
6575
6576// Applies the function macro `f` to each of the remaining parameters, inserts commas between the results,
6577// and passes userdata as the first parameter to each invocation,
6578// e.g. CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, x, a, b, c) evaluates to f(x, a), f(x, b), f(x, c)
6579#define CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, userdata, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))
6580
6581#define CATCH_REC_LIST(f, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))

6591#define INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS(param) (INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(param)) + 1)
6592#endif

6622#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN\
6623 template<typename...> struct TypeList {};\
6624 template<typename... Ts>\
6625 constexpr auto get_wrapper(Catch::Detail::priority_tag<1>) noexcept -> TypeList<Ts...> { return {}; }\
6626 template<template<typename...> class...> struct TemplateTypeList{};\
6627 template<template<typename...> class...Cs>\
6628 constexpr auto get_wrapper(Catch::Detail::priority_tag<1>) noexcept -> TemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; }\
6629 template<typename...>\
6630 struct append;\
6631 template<typename...>\
6632 struct rewrap;\
6633 template<template<typename...> class, typename...>\
6634 struct create;\
6635 template<template<typename...> class, typename>\
6636 struct convert;\
6637 \
6638 template<typename T> \
6639 struct append<T> { using type = T; };\
6640 template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, template<typename...> class L2, typename...E2, typename...Rest>\
6641 struct append<L1<E1...>, L2<E2...>, Rest...> { using type = typename append<L1<E1...,E2...>, Rest...>::type; };\
6642 template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, typename...Rest>\
6643 struct append<L1<E1...>, TypeList<mpl_::na>, Rest...> { using type = L1<E1...>; };\
6644 \
6645 template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, typename...elems>\
6646 struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<elems...>> { using type = TypeList<Container<elems...>>; };\
6647 template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, class...Elems, typename...Elements>\
6648 struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<Elems...>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<Elems...>>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
6649 \
6650 template<template <typename...> class Final, template< typename...> class...Containers, typename...Types>\
6651 struct create<Final, TemplateTypeList<Containers...>, TypeList<Types...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Containers>, Types...>::type...>::type; };\
6652 template<template <typename...> class Final, template <typename...> class List, typename...Ts>\
6653 struct convert<Final, List<Ts...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>,TypeList<Ts>...>::type; };

6655#define INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_1(signature, ...)\
6656 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> struct Nttp{};\
6657 template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)>\
6658 constexpr auto get_wrapper(Catch::Detail::priority_tag<0>) noexcept -> Nttp<__VA_ARGS__> { return {}; } \
6659 template<template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...> struct NttpTemplateTypeList{};\
6660 template<template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...Cs>\
6661 constexpr auto get_wrapper(Catch::Detail::priority_tag<0>) noexcept -> NttpTemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; } \
6662 \

6666 struct rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, List<__VA_ARGS__>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<__VA_ARGS__>>, typename rewrap<NttpTemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
6667 template<template <typename...> class Final, template<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(signature)> class...Containers, typename...Types>\

7155 #endif

7157#elif !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_PREFIX_ALL) && defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)

7355 };

7367#include <exception>

7369namespace Catch {
7370 namespace Detail {
7371 void registerTranslatorImpl(
7372 Detail::unique_ptr<IExceptionTranslator>&& translator );
7373 }
7374
7375 class ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar {
7376 template<typename T>
7377 class ExceptionTranslator : public IExceptionTranslator {
7378 public:
7379
7380 constexpr ExceptionTranslator( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) )
7381 : m_translateFunction( translateFunction )
7382 {}
7383
7384 std::string translate( ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator it, ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator itEnd ) const override {
7385#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
7386 try {
7387 if( it == itEnd )
7388 std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
7389 else
7390 return (*it)->translate( it+1, itEnd );
7391 }
7392 catch( T const& ex ) {
7393 return m_translateFunction( ex );
7394 }
7395#else
7396 return "You should never get here!";
7397#endif
7398 }
7399
7400 protected:
7401 std::string(*m_translateFunction)( T const& );
7402 };
7403
7404 public:
7405 template<typename T>
7406 ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) ) {
7407 Detail::registerTranslatorImpl(
7408 Detail::make_unique<ExceptionTranslator<T>>(
7409 translateFunction ) );
7410 }
7411 };
7412
7413} // namespace Catch
7414
7416#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION2( translatorName, signature ) \
7417 static std::string translatorName( signature ); \
7418 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
7419 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
7420 namespace{ const Catch::ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionRegistrar )( &translatorName ); } \
7421 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
7422 static std::string translatorName( signature )
7423
7424#define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION( signature ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION2( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionTranslator ), signature )
7425
7426#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
7427 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION_NO_REG( translatorName, signature) \
7428 static std::string translatorName( signature )
7429#endif
7430
7431
7432// This macro is always prefixed
7433#if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
7434#define CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION( signature ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION( signature )
7435#else
7436#define CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION( signature ) INTERNAL_CATCH_TRANSLATE_EXCEPTION_NO_REG( INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionTranslator ), signature )
7437#endif

7547 // empty string, the cache is invalidated.

7559 virtual bool next() = 0;

7629 void throw_generator_exception(char const * msg);

7632
7633 template<typename T>
7634 class IGenerator : public GeneratorUntypedBase {
7635 std::string stringifyImpl() const override {
7636 return ::Catch::Detail::stringify( get() );
7637 }
7638
7639 public:
7640 // Returns the current element of the generator
7641 //
7642 // \Precondition The generator is either freshly constructed,
7643 // or the last call to `next()` returned true
7644 virtual T const& get() const = 0;
7645 using type = T;
7646 };
7647
7648 template <typename T>
7649 using GeneratorPtr = Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<IGenerator<T>>;
7650
7651 template <typename T>
7652 class GeneratorWrapper final {
7653 GeneratorPtr<T> m_generator;
7654 public:
7656 GeneratorWrapper(IGenerator<T>* generator):
7657 m_generator(generator) {}
7658 GeneratorWrapper(GeneratorPtr<T> generator):
7659 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)) {}
7660
7661 T const& get() const {
7662 return m_generator->get();
7663 }
7664 bool next() {
7665 return m_generator->countedNext();
7666 }
7667 };
7668
7669
7670 template<typename T>
7671 class SingleValueGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7672 T m_value;
7673 public:
7674 SingleValueGenerator(T const& value) :
7675 m_value(value)
7676 {}
7677 SingleValueGenerator(T&& value):
7678 m_value(CATCH_MOVE(value))
7679 {}
7680
7681 T const& get() const override {
7682 return m_value;
7683 }
7684 bool next() override {
7685 return false;
7686 }
7687 };
7688
7689 template<typename T>
7690 class FixedValuesGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7691 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7692 "FixedValuesGenerator does not support bools because of std::vector<bool>"
7693 "specialization, use SingleValue Generator instead.");
7694 std::vector<T> m_values;
7695 size_t m_idx = 0;
7696 public:
7697 FixedValuesGenerator( std::initializer_list<T> values ) : m_values( values ) {}
7698
7699 T const& get() const override {
7700 return m_values[m_idx];
7701 }
7702 bool next() override {
7703 ++m_idx;
7704 return m_idx < m_values.size();
7705 }
7706 };
7707
7708 template <typename T, typename DecayedT = std::decay_t<T>>
7709 GeneratorWrapper<DecayedT> value( T&& value ) {
7710 return GeneratorWrapper<DecayedT>(
7711 Catch::Detail::make_unique<SingleValueGenerator<DecayedT>>(
7712 CATCH_FORWARD( value ) ) );
7713 }
7714 template <typename T>
7715 GeneratorWrapper<T> values(std::initializer_list<T> values) {
7716 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FixedValuesGenerator<T>>(values));
7717 }
7718
7719 template<typename T>
7720 class Generators : public IGenerator<T> {
7721 std::vector<GeneratorWrapper<T>> m_generators;
7722 size_t m_current = 0;
7723
7724 void add_generator( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) {
7725 m_generators.emplace_back( CATCH_MOVE( generator ) );
7726 }
7727 void add_generator( T const& val ) {
7728 m_generators.emplace_back( value( val ) );
7729 }
7730 void add_generator( T&& val ) {
7731 m_generators.emplace_back( value( CATCH_MOVE( val ) ) );
7732 }
7733 template <typename U>
7734 std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<std::decay_t<U>, T>::value>
7735 add_generator( U&& val ) {
7736 add_generator( T( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ) );
7737 }
7738
7739 template <typename U> void add_generators( U&& valueOrGenerator ) {
7740 add_generator( CATCH_FORWARD( valueOrGenerator ) );
7741 }
7742
7743 template <typename U, typename... Gs>
7744 void add_generators( U&& valueOrGenerator, Gs&&... moreGenerators ) {
7745 add_generator( CATCH_FORWARD( valueOrGenerator ) );
7746 add_generators( CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7747 }
7748
7749 public:
7750 template <typename... Gs>
7751 Generators(Gs &&... moreGenerators) {
7752 m_generators.reserve(sizeof...(Gs));
7753 add_generators(CATCH_FORWARD(moreGenerators)...);
7754 }
7755
7756 T const& get() const override {
7757 return m_generators[m_current].get();
7758 }
7759
7760 bool next() override {
7761 if (m_current >= m_generators.size()) {
7762 return false;
7763 }
7764 const bool current_status = m_generators[m_current].next();
7765 if (!current_status) {
7766 ++m_current;
7767 }
7768 return m_current < m_generators.size();
7769 }
7770 };
7771
7772
7773 template <typename... Ts>
7774 GeneratorWrapper<std::tuple<std::decay_t<Ts>...>>
7775 table( std::initializer_list<std::tuple<std::decay_t<Ts>...>> tuples ) {
7776 return values<std::tuple<Ts...>>( tuples );
7777 }
7778
7779 // Tag type to signal that a generator sequence should convert arguments to a specific type
7780 template <typename T>
7781 struct as {};
7782
7783 template<typename T, typename... Gs>
7784 auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
7785 return Generators<T>(CATCH_MOVE(generator), CATCH_FORWARD(moreGenerators)...);
7786 }
7787 template<typename T>
7788 auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) -> Generators<T> {
7789 return Generators<T>(CATCH_MOVE(generator));
7790 }
7791 template<typename T, typename... Gs>
7792 auto makeGenerators( T&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<std::decay_t<T>> {
7793 return makeGenerators( value( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ), CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7794 }
7795 template<typename T, typename U, typename... Gs>
7796 auto makeGenerators( as<T>, U&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
7797 return makeGenerators( value( T( CATCH_FORWARD( val ) ) ), CATCH_FORWARD( moreGenerators )... );
7798 }
7799
7800 IGeneratorTracker* acquireGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName,
7801 SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo );
7802 IGeneratorTracker* createGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName,
7803 SourceLineInfo lineInfo,
7804 GeneratorBasePtr&& generator );
7805
7806 template<typename L>
7807 auto generate( StringRef generatorName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, L const& generatorExpression ) -> typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type {
7808 using UnderlyingType = typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type;
7809
7810 IGeneratorTracker* tracker = acquireGeneratorTracker( generatorName, lineInfo );
7811 // Creation of tracker is delayed after generator creation, so
7812 // that constructing generator can fail without breaking everything.
7813 if (!tracker) {
7814 tracker = createGeneratorTracker(
7815 generatorName,
7816 lineInfo,
7817 Catch::Detail::make_unique<Generators<UnderlyingType>>(
7818 generatorExpression() ) );
7819 }
7820
7821 auto const& generator = static_cast<IGenerator<UnderlyingType> const&>( *tracker->getGenerator() );
7822 return generator.get();
7823 }
7824
7825} // namespace Generators
7826} // namespace Catch

7828#define CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE_IMPL( ... ) #__VA_ARGS__##_catch_sr
7829#define CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(...) CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE_IMPL(__VA_ARGS__)
7830
7831#define GENERATE( ... ) \
7832 Catch::Generators::generate( CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7833 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7834 [ ]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7835#define GENERATE_COPY( ... ) \
7836 Catch::Generators::generate( CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7837 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7838 [=]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7839#define GENERATE_REF( ... ) \
7840 Catch::Generators::generate( CATCH_INTERNAL_GENERATOR_STRINGIZE(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(generator)), \
7841 CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, \
7842 [&]{ using namespace Catch::Generators; return makeGenerators( __VA_ARGS__ ); } ) //NOLINT(google-build-using-namespace)
7843
7844#endif // CATCH_GENERATORS_HPP_INCLUDED

7847#ifndef CATCH_GENERATORS_ADAPTERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7848#define CATCH_GENERATORS_ADAPTERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7849
7850
7851#include <cassert>
7852
7853namespace Catch {
7854namespace Generators {
7855
7856 template <typename T>
7857 class TakeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7858 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7859 size_t m_returned = 0;
7860 size_t m_target;
7861 public:
7862 TakeGenerator(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7863 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7864 m_target(target)
7865 {
7866 assert(target != 0 && "Empty generators are not allowed");
7867 }
7868 T const& get() const override {
7869 return m_generator.get();
7870 }
7871 bool next() override {
7872 ++m_returned;
7873 if (m_returned >= m_target) {
7874 return false;
7875 }
7876
7877 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7878 // If the underlying generator does not contain enough values
7879 // then we cut short as well
7880 if (!success) {
7881 m_returned = m_target;
7882 }
7883 return success;
7884 }
7885 };
7886
7887 template <typename T>
7888 GeneratorWrapper<T> take(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7889 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<TakeGenerator<T>>(target, CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7890 }
7891
7892
7893 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
7894 class FilterGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7895 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7896 Predicate m_predicate;
7897 static_assert(!std::is_reference<Predicate>::value, "This would most likely result in a dangling reference");
7898 public:
7899 template <typename P>
7900 FilterGenerator(P&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7901 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7902 m_predicate(CATCH_FORWARD(pred))
7903 {
7904 if (!m_predicate(m_generator.get())) {
7905 // It might happen that there are no values that pass the
7906 // filter. In that case we throw an exception.
7907 auto has_initial_value = next();
7908 if (!has_initial_value) {
7909 Detail::throw_generator_exception("No valid value found in filtered generator");
7910 }
7911 }
7912 }
7913
7914 T const& get() const override {
7915 return m_generator.get();
7916 }
7917
7918 bool next() override {
7919 bool success = m_generator.next();
7920 if (!success) {
7921 return false;
7922 }
7923 while (!m_predicate(m_generator.get()) && (success = m_generator.next()) == true);
7924 return success;
7925 }
7926 };
7927
7928
7929 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
7930 GeneratorWrapper<T> filter(Predicate&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7931 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FilterGenerator<T, typename std::remove_reference<Predicate>::type>>(CATCH_FORWARD(pred), CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7932 }
7933
7934 template <typename T>
7935 class RepeatGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7936 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7937 "RepeatGenerator currently does not support bools"
7938 "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
7939 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7940 mutable std::vector<T> m_returned;
7941 size_t m_target_repeats;
7942 size_t m_current_repeat = 0;
7943 size_t m_repeat_index = 0;
7944 public:
7945 RepeatGenerator(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7946 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
7947 m_target_repeats(repeats)
7948 {
7949 assert(m_target_repeats > 0 && "Repeat generator must repeat at least once");
7950 }
7951
7952 T const& get() const override {
7953 if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7954 m_returned.push_back(m_generator.get());
7955 return m_returned.back();
7956 }
7957 return m_returned[m_repeat_index];
7958 }
7959
7960 bool next() override {
7961 // There are 2 basic cases:
7962 // 1) We are still reading the generator
7963 // 2) We are reading our own cache
7964
7965 // In the first case, we need to poke the underlying generator.
7966 // If it happily moves, we are left in that state, otherwise it is time to start reading from our cache
7967 if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7968 const auto success = m_generator.next();
7969 if (!success) {
7970 ++m_current_repeat;
7971 }
7972 return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7973 }
7974
7975 // In the second case, we need to move indices forward and check that we haven't run up against the end
7976 ++m_repeat_index;
7977 if (m_repeat_index == m_returned.size()) {
7978 m_repeat_index = 0;
7979 ++m_current_repeat;
7980 }
7981 return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7982 }
7983 };
7984
7985 template <typename T>
7986 GeneratorWrapper<T> repeat(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7987 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RepeatGenerator<T>>(repeats, CATCH_MOVE(generator)));
7988 }
7989
7990 template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
7991 class MapGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7992 // TBD: provide static assert for mapping function, for friendly error message
7993 GeneratorWrapper<U> m_generator;
7994 Func m_function;
7995 // To avoid returning dangling reference, we have to save the values
7996 T m_cache;
7997 public:
7998 template <typename F2 = Func>
7999 MapGenerator(F2&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) :
8000 m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator)),
8001 m_function(CATCH_FORWARD(function)),
8002 m_cache(m_function(m_generator.get()))
8003 {}
8004
8005 T const& get() const override {
8006 return m_cache;
8007 }
8008 bool next() override {
8009 const auto success = m_generator.next();
8010 if (success) {
8011 m_cache = m_function(m_generator.get());
8012 }
8013 return success;
8014 }
8015 };
8016
8017 template <typename Func, typename U, typename T = FunctionReturnType<Func, U>>
8018 GeneratorWrapper<T> map(Func&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) {
8019 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8020 Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(CATCH_FORWARD(function), CATCH_MOVE(generator))
8021 );
8022 }
8023
8024 template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
8025 GeneratorWrapper<T> map(Func&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) {
8026 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8027 Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(CATCH_FORWARD(function), CATCH_MOVE(generator))
8028 );
8029 }
8030
8031 template <typename T>
8032 class ChunkGenerator final : public IGenerator<std::vector<T>> {
8033 std::vector<T> m_chunk;
8034 size_t m_chunk_size;
8035 GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
8036 bool m_used_up = false;
8037 public:
8038 ChunkGenerator(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T> generator) :
8039 m_chunk_size(size), m_generator(CATCH_MOVE(generator))
8040 {
8041 m_chunk.reserve(m_chunk_size);
8042 if (m_chunk_size != 0) {
8043 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
8044 for (size_t i = 1; i < m_chunk_size; ++i) {
8045 if (!m_generator.next()) {
8046 Detail::throw_generator_exception("Not enough values to initialize the first chunk");
8047 }
8048 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
8049 }
8050 }
8051 }
8052 std::vector<T> const& get() const override {
8053 return m_chunk;
8054 }
8055 bool next() override {
8056 m_chunk.clear();
8057 for (size_t idx = 0; idx < m_chunk_size; ++idx) {
8058 if (!m_generator.next()) {
8059 return false;
8060 }
8061 m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
8062 }
8063 return true;
8064 }
8065 };
8066
8067 template <typename T>
8068 GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>> chunk(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
8069 return GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>>(
8070 Catch::Detail::make_unique<ChunkGenerator<T>>(size, CATCH_MOVE(generator))
8071 );
8072 }

8091namespace Catch {
8092
8093 // This is a simple implementation of C++11 Uniform Random Number
8094 // Generator. It does not provide all operators, because Catch2
8095 // does not use it, but it should behave as expected inside stdlib's
8096 // distributions.
8097 // The implementation is based on the PCG family (http://pcg-random.org)
8098 class SimplePcg32 {
8099 using state_type = std::uint64_t;
8100 public:
8101 using result_type = std::uint32_t;
8102 static constexpr result_type (min)() {
8103 return 0;
8104 }
8105 static constexpr result_type (max)() {
8106 return static_cast<result_type>(-1);
8107 }
8108
8109 // Provide some default initial state for the default constructor
8110 SimplePcg32():SimplePcg32(0xed743cc4U) {}
8111
8112 explicit SimplePcg32(result_type seed_);
8113
8114 void seed(result_type seed_);
8115 void discard(uint64_t skip);
8116
8117 result_type operator()();
8118
8119 private:
8120 friend bool operator==(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
8121 friend bool operator!=(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
8122
8123 // In theory we also need operator<< and operator>>
8124 // In practice we do not use them, so we will skip them for now
8125
8126
8127 std::uint64_t m_state;
8128 // This part of the state determines which "stream" of the numbers
8129 // is chosen -- we take it as a constant for Catch2, so we only
8130 // need to deal with seeding the main state.
8131 // Picked by reading 8 bytes from `/dev/random` :-)
8132 static const std::uint64_t s_inc = (0x13ed0cc53f939476ULL << 1ULL) | 1ULL;
8133 };
8134
8135} // end namespace Catch

8150#include <climits>
8151#include <cstddef>
8152#include <cstdint>
8153#include <type_traits>

8155// Note: We use the usual enable-disable-autodetect dance here even though
8156// we do not support these in CMake configuration options (yet?).
8157// It is highly unlikely that we will need to make these actually
8158// user-configurable, but this will make it simpler if weend up needing
8159// it, and it provides an escape hatch to the users who need it.
8160#if defined( __SIZEOF_INT128__ )
8161# define CATCH_CONFIG_INTERNAL_UINT128
8162// Unlike GCC, MSVC does not polyfill umul as mulh + mul pair on ARM machines.
8163// Currently we do not bother doing this ourselves, but we could if it became
8164// important for perf.
8165#elif defined( _MSC_VER ) && defined( _M_X64 )
8166# define CATCH_CONFIG_INTERNAL_MSVC_UMUL128
8167#endif
8168
8169#if defined( CATCH_CONFIG_INTERNAL_UINT128 ) && \
8170 !defined( CATCH_CONFIG_NO_UINT128 ) && \
8171 !defined( CATCH_CONFIG_UINT128 )
8172#define CATCH_CONFIG_UINT128
8173#endif
8174
8175#if defined( CATCH_CONFIG_INTERNAL_MSVC_UMUL128 ) && \
8176 !defined( CATCH_CONFIG_NO_MSVC_UMUL128 ) && \
8177 !defined( CATCH_CONFIG_MSVC_UMUL128 )
8178# define CATCH_CONFIG_MSVC_UMUL128
8179# include <intrin.h>
8180#endif

8183namespace Catch {
8184 namespace Detail {
8185
8186 template <std::size_t>
8187 struct SizedUnsignedType;
8188#define SizedUnsignedTypeHelper( TYPE ) \
8189 template <> \
8190 struct SizedUnsignedType<sizeof( TYPE )> { \
8191 using type = TYPE; \
8192 }
8193
8194 SizedUnsignedTypeHelper( std::uint8_t );
8195 SizedUnsignedTypeHelper( std::uint16_t );
8196 SizedUnsignedTypeHelper( std::uint32_t );
8197 SizedUnsignedTypeHelper( std::uint64_t );
8198#undef SizedUnsignedTypeHelper
8199
8200 template <std::size_t sz>
8201 using SizedUnsignedType_t = typename SizedUnsignedType<sz>::type;
8202
8203 template <typename T>
8204 using DoubleWidthUnsignedType_t = SizedUnsignedType_t<2 * sizeof( T )>;
8205
8206 template <typename T>
8207 struct ExtendedMultResult {
8208 T upper;
8209 T lower;
8210 constexpr bool operator==( ExtendedMultResult const& rhs ) const {
8211 return upper == rhs.upper && lower == rhs.lower;
8212 }
8213 };
8214
8221 constexpr ExtendedMultResult<std::uint64_t>
8222 extendedMultPortable(std::uint64_t lhs, std::uint64_t rhs) {
8223#define CarryBits( x ) ( x >> 32 )
8224#define Digits( x ) ( x & 0xFF'FF'FF'FF )
8225 std::uint64_t lhs_low = Digits( lhs );
8226 std::uint64_t rhs_low = Digits( rhs );
8227 std::uint64_t low_low = ( lhs_low * rhs_low );
8228 std::uint64_t high_high = CarryBits( lhs ) * CarryBits( rhs );
8229
8230 // We add in carry bits from low-low already
8231 std::uint64_t high_low =
8232 ( CarryBits( lhs ) * rhs_low ) + CarryBits( low_low );
8233 // Note that we can add only low bits from high_low, to avoid
8234 // overflow with large inputs
8235 std::uint64_t low_high =
8236 ( lhs_low * CarryBits( rhs ) ) + Digits( high_low );
8237
8238 return { high_high + CarryBits( high_low ) + CarryBits( low_high ),
8239 ( low_high << 32 ) | Digits( low_low ) };
8240#undef CarryBits
8241#undef Digits
8242 }
8243
8245 inline ExtendedMultResult<std::uint64_t>
8246 extendedMult( std::uint64_t lhs, std::uint64_t rhs ) {
8247#if defined( CATCH_CONFIG_UINT128 )
8248 auto result = __uint128_t( lhs ) * __uint128_t( rhs );
8249 return { static_cast<std::uint64_t>( result >> 64 ),
8250 static_cast<std::uint64_t>( result ) };
8251#elif defined( CATCH_CONFIG_MSVC_UMUL128 )
8252 std::uint64_t high;
8253 std::uint64_t low = _umul128( lhs, rhs, &high );
8254 return { high, low };
8255#else
8256 return extendedMultPortable( lhs, rhs );
8257#endif
8258 }
8259
8260
8261 template <typename UInt>
8262 constexpr ExtendedMultResult<UInt> extendedMult( UInt lhs, UInt rhs ) {
8263 static_assert( std::is_unsigned<UInt>::value,
8264 "extendedMult can only handle unsigned integers" );
8265 static_assert( sizeof( UInt ) < sizeof( std::uint64_t ),
8266 "Generic extendedMult can only handle types smaller "
8267 "than uint64_t" );
8268 using WideType = DoubleWidthUnsignedType_t<UInt>;
8269
8270 auto result = WideType( lhs ) * WideType( rhs );
8271 return {
8272 static_cast<UInt>( result >> ( CHAR_BIT * sizeof( UInt ) ) ),
8273 static_cast<UInt>( result & UInt( -1 ) ) };
8274 }
8275
8276
8277 template <typename TargetType,
8278 typename Generator>
8279 std::enable_if_t<sizeof(typename Generator::result_type) >= sizeof(TargetType),
8280 TargetType> fillBitsFrom(Generator& gen) {
8281 using gresult_type = typename Generator::result_type;
8282 static_assert( std::is_unsigned<TargetType>::value, "Only unsigned integers are supported" );
8283 static_assert( Generator::min() == 0 &&
8284 Generator::max() == static_cast<gresult_type>( -1 ),
8285 "Generator must be able to output all numbers in its result type (effectively it must be a random bit generator)" );
8286
8287 // We want to return the top bits from a generator, as they are
8288 // usually considered higher quality.
8289 constexpr auto generated_bits = sizeof( gresult_type ) * CHAR_BIT;
8290 constexpr auto return_bits = sizeof( TargetType ) * CHAR_BIT;
8291
8292 return static_cast<TargetType>( gen() >>
8293 ( generated_bits - return_bits) );
8294 }
8295
8296 template <typename TargetType,
8297 typename Generator>
8298 std::enable_if_t<sizeof(typename Generator::result_type) < sizeof(TargetType),
8299 TargetType> fillBitsFrom(Generator& gen) {
8300 using gresult_type = typename Generator::result_type;
8301 static_assert( std::is_unsigned<TargetType>::value,
8302 "Only unsigned integers are supported" );
8303 static_assert( Generator::min() == 0 &&
8304 Generator::max() == static_cast<gresult_type>( -1 ),
8305 "Generator must be able to output all numbers in its result type (effectively it must be a random bit generator)" );
8306
8307 constexpr auto generated_bits = sizeof( gresult_type ) * CHAR_BIT;
8308 constexpr auto return_bits = sizeof( TargetType ) * CHAR_BIT;
8309 std::size_t filled_bits = 0;
8310 TargetType ret = 0;
8311 do {
8312 ret <<= generated_bits;
8313 ret |= gen();
8314 filled_bits += generated_bits;
8315 } while ( filled_bits < return_bits );
8316
8317 return ret;
8318 }
8319
8320 /*
8321 * Transposes numbers into unsigned type while keeping their ordering
8322 *
8323 * This means that signed types are changed so that the ordering is
8324 * [INT_MIN, ..., -1, 0, ..., INT_MAX], rather than order we would
8325 * get by simple casting ([0, ..., INT_MAX, INT_MIN, ..., -1])
8326 */
8327 template <typename OriginalType, typename UnsignedType>
8328 constexpr
8329 std::enable_if_t<std::is_signed<OriginalType>::value, UnsignedType>
8330 transposeToNaturalOrder( UnsignedType in ) {
8331 static_assert(
8332 sizeof( OriginalType ) == sizeof( UnsignedType ),
8333 "reordering requires the same sized types on both sides" );
8334 static_assert( std::is_unsigned<UnsignedType>::value,
8335 "Input type must be unsigned" );
8336 // Assuming 2s complement (standardized in current C++), the
8337 // positive and negative numbers are already internally ordered,
8338 // and their difference is in the top bit. Swapping it orders
8339 // them the desired way.
8340 constexpr auto highest_bit =
8341 UnsignedType( 1 ) << ( sizeof( UnsignedType ) * CHAR_BIT - 1 );
8342 return static_cast<UnsignedType>( in ^ highest_bit );
8343 }
8344
8345
8346
8347 template <typename OriginalType,
8348 typename UnsignedType>
8349 constexpr
8350 std::enable_if_t<std::is_unsigned<OriginalType>::value, UnsignedType>
8351 transposeToNaturalOrder(UnsignedType in) {
8352 static_assert(
8353 sizeof( OriginalType ) == sizeof( UnsignedType ),
8354 "reordering requires the same sized types on both sides" );
8355 static_assert( std::is_unsigned<UnsignedType>::value, "Input type must be unsigned" );
8356 // No reordering is needed for unsigned -> unsigned
8357 return in;
8358 }
8359 } // namespace Detail
8360} // namespace Catch
8361
8362#endif // CATCH_RANDOM_INTEGER_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
8363
8364namespace Catch {
8365
8377template <typename IntegerType>
8378class uniform_integer_distribution {
8379 static_assert(std::is_integral<IntegerType>::value, "...");
8380
8381 using UnsignedIntegerType = Detail::SizedUnsignedType_t<sizeof(IntegerType)>;
8382
8383 // Only the left bound is stored, and we store it converted to its
8384 // unsigned image. This avoids having to do the conversions inside
8385 // the operator(), at the cost of having to do the conversion in
8386 // the a() getter. The right bound is only needed in the b() getter,
8387 // so we recompute it there from other stored data.
8388 UnsignedIntegerType m_a;
8389
8390 // How many different values are there in [a, b]. a == b => 1, can be 0 for distribution over all values in the type.
8391 UnsignedIntegerType m_ab_distance;
8392
8393 // We hoisted this out of the main generation function. Technically,
8394 // this means that using this distribution will be slower than Lemire's
8395 // algorithm if this distribution instance will be used only few times,
8396 // but it will be faster if it is used many times. Since Catch2 uses
8397 // distributions only to implement random generators, we assume that each
8398 // distribution will be reused many times and this is an optimization.
8399 UnsignedIntegerType m_rejection_threshold = 0;
8400
8401 static constexpr UnsignedIntegerType computeDistance(IntegerType a, IntegerType b) {
8402 // This overflows and returns 0 if a == 0 and b == TYPE_MAX.
8403 // We handle that later when generating the number.
8404 return transposeTo(b) - transposeTo(a) + 1;
8405 }
8406
8407 static constexpr UnsignedIntegerType computeRejectionThreshold(UnsignedIntegerType ab_distance) {
8408 // distance == 0 means that we will return all possible values from
8409 // the type's range, and that we shouldn't reject anything.
8410 if ( ab_distance == 0 ) { return 0; }
8411 return ( ~ab_distance + 1 ) % ab_distance;
8412 }
8413
8414 static constexpr UnsignedIntegerType transposeTo(IntegerType in) {
8415 return Detail::transposeToNaturalOrder<IntegerType>(
8416 static_cast<UnsignedIntegerType>( in ) );
8417 }
8418 static constexpr IntegerType transposeBack(UnsignedIntegerType in) {
8419 return static_cast<IntegerType>(
8420 Detail::transposeToNaturalOrder<IntegerType>(in) );
8421 }
8422
8423public:
8424 using result_type = IntegerType;
8425
8426 constexpr uniform_integer_distribution( IntegerType a, IntegerType b ):
8427 m_a( transposeTo(a) ),
8428 m_ab_distance( computeDistance(a, b) ),
8429 m_rejection_threshold( computeRejectionThreshold(m_ab_distance) ) {
8430 assert( a <= b );
8431 }
8432
8433 template <typename Generator>
8434 constexpr result_type operator()( Generator& g ) {
8435 // All possible values of result_type are valid.
8436 if ( m_ab_distance == 0 ) {
8437 return transposeBack( Detail::fillBitsFrom<UnsignedIntegerType>( g ) );
8438 }
8439
8440 auto random_number = Detail::fillBitsFrom<UnsignedIntegerType>( g );
8441 auto emul = Detail::extendedMult( random_number, m_ab_distance );
8442 // Unlike Lemire's algorithm we skip the ab_distance check, since
8443 // we precomputed the rejection threshold, which is always tighter.
8444 while (emul.lower < m_rejection_threshold) {
8445 random_number = Detail::fillBitsFrom<UnsignedIntegerType>( g );
8446 emul = Detail::extendedMult( random_number, m_ab_distance );
8447 }
8448
8449 return transposeBack(m_a + emul.upper);
8450 }
8451
8452 constexpr result_type a() const { return transposeBack(m_a); }
8453 constexpr result_type b() const { return transposeBack(m_ab_distance + m_a - 1); }
8454};
8455
8456} // end namespace Catch

8496 namespace Detail {
8502 template <typename FloatType>
8503 FloatType gamma(FloatType a, FloatType b) {
8504 static_assert( std::is_floating_point<FloatType>::value,
8505 "gamma returns the largest ULP magnitude within "
8506 "floating point range [a, b]. This only makes sense "
8507 "for floating point types" );
8508 assert( a <= b );
8509
8510 const auto gamma_up = Catch::nextafter( a, std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::infinity() ) - a;
8511 const auto gamma_down = b - Catch::nextafter( b, -std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::infinity() );
8512
8513 return gamma_up < gamma_down ? gamma_down : gamma_up;
8514 }
8515
8516 template <typename FloatingPoint>
8517 struct DistanceTypePicker;
8518 template <>
8519 struct DistanceTypePicker<float> {
8520 using type = std::uint32_t;
8521 };
8522 template <>
8523 struct DistanceTypePicker<double> {
8524 using type = std::uint64_t;
8525 };
8526
8527 template <typename T>
8528 using DistanceType = typename DistanceTypePicker<T>::type;
8529
8530#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
8531# pragma GCC diagnostic push
8532# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
8533#endif
8543 template <typename FloatType>
8544 DistanceType<FloatType>
8545 count_equidistant_floats( FloatType a, FloatType b, FloatType distance ) {
8546 assert( a <= b );
8547 // We get distance as gamma for our uniform float distribution,
8548 // so this will round perfectly.
8549 const auto ag = a / distance;
8550 const auto bg = b / distance;
8551
8552 const auto s = bg - ag;
8553 const auto err = ( std::fabs( a ) <= std::fabs( b ) )
8554 ? -ag - ( s - bg )
8555 : bg - ( s + ag );
8556 const auto ceil_s = static_cast<DistanceType<FloatType>>( std::ceil( s ) );
8557
8558 return ( ceil_s != s ) ? ceil_s : ceil_s + ( err > 0 );
8559 }
8560#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
8561# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
8562#endif
8563
8564 }
8565
8566} // end namespace Catch
8567
8568#endif // CATCH_RANDOM_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
8569
8570#include <cmath>
8571#include <type_traits>
8572
8573namespace Catch {
8574
8575 namespace Detail {
8576#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
8577# pragma GCC diagnostic push
8578# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
8579#endif
8580 // The issue with overflow only happens with maximal ULP and HUGE
8581 // distance, e.g. when generating numbers in [-inf, inf] for given
8582 // type. So we only check for the largest possible ULP in the
8583 // type, and return something that does not overflow to inf in 1 mult.
8584 constexpr std::uint64_t calculate_max_steps_in_one_go(double gamma) {
8585 if ( gamma == 1.99584030953472e+292 ) { return 9007199254740991; }
8586 return static_cast<std::uint64_t>( -1 );
8587 }
8588 constexpr std::uint32_t calculate_max_steps_in_one_go(float gamma) {
8589 if ( gamma == 2.028241e+31f ) { return 16777215; }
8590 return static_cast<std::uint32_t>( -1 );
8591 }
8592#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
8593# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
8594#endif
8595 }
8596
8623template <typename FloatType>
8624class uniform_floating_point_distribution {
8625 static_assert(std::is_floating_point<FloatType>::value, "...");
8626 static_assert(!std::is_same<FloatType, long double>::value,
8627 "We do not support long double due to inconsistent behaviour between platforms");
8628
8629 using WidthType = Detail::DistanceType<FloatType>;
8630
8631 FloatType m_a, m_b;
8632 FloatType m_ulp_magnitude;
8633 WidthType m_floats_in_range;
8634 uniform_integer_distribution<WidthType> m_int_dist;
8635
8636 // In specific cases, we can overflow into `inf` when computing the
8637 // `steps * g` offset. To avoid this, we don't offset by more than this
8638 // in one multiply + addition.
8639 WidthType m_max_steps_in_one_go;
8640 // We don't want to do the magnitude check every call to `operator()`
8641 bool m_a_has_leq_magnitude;
8642
8643public:
8644 using result_type = FloatType;
8645
8646 uniform_floating_point_distribution( FloatType a, FloatType b ):
8647 m_a( a ),
8648 m_b( b ),
8649 m_ulp_magnitude( Detail::gamma( m_a, m_b ) ),
8650 m_floats_in_range( Detail::count_equidistant_floats( m_a, m_b, m_ulp_magnitude ) ),
8651 m_int_dist(0, m_floats_in_range),
8652 m_max_steps_in_one_go( Detail::calculate_max_steps_in_one_go(m_ulp_magnitude)),
8653 m_a_has_leq_magnitude(std::fabs(m_a) <= std::fabs(m_b))
8654 {
8655 assert( a <= b );
8656 }
8657
8658 template <typename Generator>
8659 result_type operator()( Generator& g ) {
8660 WidthType steps = m_int_dist( g );
8661 if ( m_a_has_leq_magnitude ) {
8662 if ( steps == m_floats_in_range ) { return m_a; }
8663 auto b = m_b;
8664 while (steps > m_max_steps_in_one_go) {
8665 b -= m_max_steps_in_one_go * m_ulp_magnitude;
8666 steps -= m_max_steps_in_one_go;
8667 }
8668 return b - steps * m_ulp_magnitude;
8669 } else {
8670 if ( steps == m_floats_in_range ) { return m_b; }
8671 auto a = m_a;
8672 while (steps > m_max_steps_in_one_go) {
8673 a += m_max_steps_in_one_go * m_ulp_magnitude;
8674 steps -= m_max_steps_in_one_go;
8675 }
8676 return a + steps * m_ulp_magnitude;
8677 }
8678 }
8679
8680 result_type a() const { return m_a; }
8681 result_type b() const { return m_b; }
8682};
8683
8684} // end namespace Catch
8685
8686#endif // CATCH_UNIFORM_FLOATING_POINT_DISTRIBUTION_HPP_INCLUDED
8687
8688namespace Catch {
8689namespace Generators {
8690namespace Detail {
8691 // Returns a suitable seed for a random floating generator based off
8692 // the primary internal rng. It does so by taking current value from
8693 // the rng and returning it as the seed.
8694 std::uint32_t getSeed();
8695}
8696
8697template <typename Float>
8698class RandomFloatingGenerator final : public IGenerator<Float> {
8699 Catch::SimplePcg32 m_rng;
8700 Catch::uniform_floating_point_distribution<Float> m_dist;
8701 Float m_current_number;
8702public:
8703 RandomFloatingGenerator( Float a, Float b, std::uint32_t seed ):
8704 m_rng(seed),
8705 m_dist(a, b) {
8706 static_cast<void>(next());
8707 }
8708
8709 Float const& get() const override {
8710 return m_current_number;
8711 }
8712 bool next() override {
8713 m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
8714 return true;
8715 }
8716};
8717
8718template <>
8719class RandomFloatingGenerator<long double> final : public IGenerator<long double> {
8720 // We still rely on <random> for this specialization, but we don't
8721 // want to drag it into the header.
8722 struct PImpl;
8723 Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<PImpl> m_pimpl;
8724 long double m_current_number;
8725
8726public:
8727 RandomFloatingGenerator( long double a, long double b, std::uint32_t seed );
8728
8729 long double const& get() const override { return m_current_number; }
8730 bool next() override;
8731
8732 ~RandomFloatingGenerator() override; // = default
8733};
8734
8735template <typename Integer>
8736class RandomIntegerGenerator final : public IGenerator<Integer> {
8737 Catch::SimplePcg32 m_rng;
8738 Catch::uniform_integer_distribution<Integer> m_dist;
8739 Integer m_current_number;
8740public:
8741 RandomIntegerGenerator( Integer a, Integer b, std::uint32_t seed ):
8742 m_rng(seed),
8743 m_dist(a, b) {
8744 static_cast<void>(next());
8745 }
8746
8747 Integer const& get() const override {
8748 return m_current_number;
8749 }
8750 bool next() override {
8751 m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
8752 return true;
8753 }
8754};
8755
8756template <typename T>
8757std::enable_if_t<std::is_integral<T>::value, GeneratorWrapper<T>>
8758random(T a, T b) {
8759 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8760 Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomIntegerGenerator<T>>(a, b, Detail::getSeed())
8761 );
8762}
8763
8764template <typename T>
8765std::enable_if_t<std::is_floating_point<T>::value,
8766GeneratorWrapper<T>>
8767random(T a, T b) {
8768 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
8769 Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomFloatingGenerator<T>>(a, b, Detail::getSeed())
8770 );
8771}

8791
8792template <typename T>
8793class RangeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
8794 T m_current;
8795 T m_end;
8796 T m_step;
8797 bool m_positive;
8798
8799public:
8800 RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step):
8801 m_current(start),
8802 m_end(end),
8803 m_step(step),
8804 m_positive(m_step > T(0))
8805 {
8806 assert(m_current != m_end && "Range start and end cannot be equal");
8807 assert(m_step != T(0) && "Step size cannot be zero");
8808 assert(((m_positive && m_current <= m_end) || (!m_positive && m_current >= m_end)) && "Step moves away from end");
8809 }
8810
8811 RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end):
8812 RangeGenerator(start, end, (start < end) ? T(1) : T(-1))
8813 {}
8814
8815 T const& get() const override {
8816 return m_current;
8817 }
8818
8819 bool next() override {
8820 m_current += m_step;
8821 return (m_positive) ? (m_current < m_end) : (m_current > m_end);
8822 }
8823};
8824
8825template <typename T>
8826GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step) {
8827 static_assert(std::is_arithmetic<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be numeric");
8828 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end, step));
8829}
8830
8831template <typename T>
8832GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end) {
8833 static_assert(std::is_integral<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be an integer");
8834 return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end));
8835}
8836
8837
8838template <typename T>
8839class IteratorGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
8840 static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
8841 "IteratorGenerator currently does not support bools"
8842 "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
8843
8844 std::vector<T> m_elems;
8845 size_t m_current = 0;
8846public:
8847 template <typename InputIterator, typename InputSentinel>
8848 IteratorGenerator(InputIterator first, InputSentinel last):m_elems(first, last) {
8849 if (m_elems.empty()) {
8850 Detail::throw_generator_exception("IteratorGenerator received no valid values");
8851 }
8852 }
8853
8854 T const& get() const override {
8855 return m_elems[m_current];
8856 }
8857
8858 bool next() override {
8859 ++m_current;
8860 return m_current != m_elems.size();
8861 }
8862};
8863
8864template <typename InputIterator,
8865 typename InputSentinel,
8866 typename ResultType = std::remove_const_t<typename std::iterator_traits<InputIterator>::value_type>>
8867GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(InputIterator from, InputSentinel to) {
8868 return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(from, to));
8869}
8870
8871template <typename Container>
8872auto from_range(Container const& cnt) {
8873 using std::begin;
8874 using std::end;
8875 return from_range( begin( cnt ), end( cnt ) );
8876}

9313 struct Colour {
9314 enum Code {
9315 None = 0,
9316
9317 White,
9318 Red,
9319 Green,
9320 Blue,
9321 Cyan,
9322 Yellow,
9323 Grey,
9324
9325 Bright = 0x10,
9326
9327 BrightRed = Bright | Red,
9328 BrightGreen = Bright | Green,
9329 LightGrey = Bright | Grey,
9330 BrightWhite = Bright | White,
9331 BrightYellow = Bright | Yellow,
9332

9337 ResultSuccess = BrightGreen,
9338 ResultExpectedFailure = Warning,
9339
9340 Error = BrightRed,
9341 Success = Green,
9342 Skip = LightGrey,

9345 ReconstructedExpression = BrightYellow,

9352 class ColourImpl {
9353 protected:
9355 IStream* m_stream;
9356 public:
9357 ColourImpl( IStream* stream ): m_stream( stream ) {}
9358
9361 class ColourGuard {
9362 ColourImpl const* m_colourImpl;
9363 Colour::Code m_code;
9364 bool m_engaged = false;
9365
9366 public:
9368 ColourGuard( Colour::Code code,
9369 ColourImpl const* colour );
9370

9372 ColourGuard& operator=( ColourGuard const& rhs ) = delete;
9373
9374 ColourGuard( ColourGuard&& rhs ) noexcept;
9375 ColourGuard& operator=( ColourGuard&& rhs ) noexcept;
9376
9378 ~ColourGuard();
9379
9385 ColourGuard& engage( std::ostream& stream ) &;
9391 ColourGuard&& engage( std::ostream& stream ) &&;
9392
9393 private:

9396 ColourGuard& guard ) {
9397 guard.engageImpl( lhs );
9398 return lhs;
9399 }
9400

9402 ColourGuard&& guard) {
9403 guard.engageImpl( lhs );
9404 return lhs;
9405 }
9406
9407 void engageImpl( std::ostream& stream );
9408
9409 };

9411 virtual ~ColourImpl(); // = default
9418 ColourGuard guardColour( Colour::Code colourCode );
9419
9420 private:

9422 };

9536#if !defined( CATCH_TRAP ) && defined( __clang__ ) && defined( __has_builtin )

9538# define CATCH_TRAP() __builtin_debugtrap()

9544#endif
9545
9546#if !defined(CATCH_TRAP) // If we couldn't use compiler-specific impl from above, we get into platform-specific options
9547#ifdef CATCH_PLATFORM_MAC
9548
9549 #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
9550 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3\n" : : ) /* NOLINT */
9551 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
9552 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd43e0000")
9553 #elif defined(__POWERPC__)
9554 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("li r0, 20\nsc\nnop\nli r0, 37\nli r4, 2\nsc\nnop\n" \
9555 : : : "memory","r0","r3","r4" ) /* NOLINT */
9556 #endif
9557
9558#elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_IPHONE)
9559
9560 // use inline assembler
9561 #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)

9563 #elif defined(__aarch64__)
9564 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd4200000")
9565 #elif defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
9566 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xe7f001f0")
9567 #elif defined(__arm__) && defined(__thumb__)
9568 #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xde01")
9569 #endif
9570
9571#elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_LINUX) || defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_QNX)
9572 // If we can use inline assembler, do it because this allows us to break
9573 // directly at the location of the failing check instead of breaking inside
9574 // raise() called from it, i.e. one stack frame below.
9575 #if defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386) || defined(__x86_64))
9576 #define CATCH_TRAP() asm volatile ("int $3") /* NOLINT */
9577 #else // Fall back to the generic way.
9578 #include <signal.h>
9579
9580 #define CATCH_TRAP() raise(SIGTRAP)
9581 #endif
9582#elif defined(__MINGW32__)
9583 extern "C" __declspec(dllimport) void __stdcall DebugBreak();

9585#endif
9586#endif // ^^ CATCH_TRAP is not defined yet, so we define it

9723namespace Catch {
9724
9735 class FatalConditionHandler {
9736 bool m_started = false;
9737
9738 // Install/disengage implementation for specific platform.
9739 // Should be if-defed to work on current platform, can assume
9740 // engage-disengage 1:1 pairing.
9741 void engage_platform();
9742 void disengage_platform() noexcept;
9743 public:
9744 // Should also have platform-specific implementations as needed
9745 FatalConditionHandler();
9746 ~FatalConditionHandler();
9747
9748 void engage() {
9749 assert(!m_started && "Handler cannot be installed twice.");
9750 m_started = true;
9751 engage_platform();
9752 }
9753
9754 void disengage() noexcept {
9755 assert(m_started && "Handler cannot be uninstalled without being installed first");
9756 m_started = false;
9757 disengage_platform();
9758 }
9759 };
9760
9762 class FatalConditionHandlerGuard {
9763 FatalConditionHandler* m_handler;
9764 public:
9765 FatalConditionHandlerGuard(FatalConditionHandler* handler):
9766 m_handler(handler) {
9767 m_handler->engage();
9768 }
9769 ~FatalConditionHandlerGuard() {
9770 m_handler->disengage();
9771 }
9772 };

9779#ifndef CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
9780#define CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
9781
9782
9783#include <cassert>
9784#include <cmath>
9785#include <cstdint>
9786#include <utility>
9787#include <limits>
9788
9789namespace Catch {
9790 namespace Detail {
9791
9792 uint32_t convertToBits(float f);
9793 uint64_t convertToBits(double d);
9794
9795 // Used when we know we want == comparison of two doubles
9796 // to centralize warning suppression
9797 bool directCompare( float lhs, float rhs );
9798 bool directCompare( double lhs, double rhs );
9799
9800 } // end namespace Detail
9801
9802
9803
9804#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
9805# pragma GCC diagnostic push
9806 // We do a bunch of direct compensations of floating point numbers,
9807 // because we know what we are doing and actually do want the direct
9808 // comparison behaviour.
9809# pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
9810#endif
9811
9829 template <typename FP>
9830 uint64_t ulpDistance( FP lhs, FP rhs ) {
9831 assert( std::numeric_limits<FP>::is_iec559 &&
9832 "ulpDistance assumes IEEE-754 format for floating point types" );
9833 assert( !Catch::isnan( lhs ) &&
9834 "Distance between NaN and number is not meaningful" );
9835 assert( !Catch::isnan( rhs ) &&
9836 "Distance between NaN and number is not meaningful" );
9837
9838 // We want X == Y to imply 0 ULP distance even if X and Y aren't
9839 // bit-equal (-0 and 0), or X - Y != 0 (same sign infinities).
9840 if ( lhs == rhs ) { return 0; }
9841
9842 // We need a properly typed positive zero for type inference.
9843 static constexpr FP positive_zero{};
9844
9845 // We want to ensure that +/- 0 is always represented as positive zero
9846 if ( lhs == positive_zero ) { lhs = positive_zero; }
9847 if ( rhs == positive_zero ) { rhs = positive_zero; }
9848
9849 // If arguments have different signs, we can handle them by summing
9850 // how far are they from 0 each.
9851 if ( std::signbit( lhs ) != std::signbit( rhs ) ) {
9852 return ulpDistance( std::abs( lhs ), positive_zero ) +
9853 ulpDistance( std::abs( rhs ), positive_zero );
9854 }
9855
9856 // When both lhs and rhs are of the same sign, we can just
9857 // read the numbers bitwise as integers, and then subtract them
9858 // (assuming IEEE).
9859 uint64_t lc = Detail::convertToBits( lhs );
9860 uint64_t rc = Detail::convertToBits( rhs );
9861
9862 // The ulp distance between two numbers is symmetric, so to avoid
9863 // dealing with overflows we want the bigger converted number on the lhs
9864 if ( lc < rc ) {
9865 std::swap( lc, rc );
9866 }
9867
9868 return lc - rc;
9869 }
9870
9871#if defined( __GNUC__ ) || defined( __clang__ )
9872# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
9873#endif
9874
9875
9876} // end namespace Catch
9877
9878#endif // CATCH_FLOATING_POINT_HELPERS_HPP_INCLUDED
9879

9882#define CATCH_GETENV_HPP_INCLUDED

9890}
9891}

9893#endif // CATCH_GETENV_HPP_INCLUDED
