9896#ifndef CATCH_IS_PERMUTATION_HPP_INCLUDED
9897#define CATCH_IS_PERMUTATION_HPP_INCLUDED
9898
9899#include <iterator>
9900#include <type_traits>
9901
9902namespace Catch {
9903 namespace Detail {
9904
9905 template <typename ForwardIter,
9906 typename Sentinel,
9907 typename T,
9908 typename Comparator>
9909 constexpr
9910 ForwardIter find_sentinel( ForwardIter start,
9911 Sentinel sentinel,
9912 T const& value,
9913 Comparator cmp ) {
9914 while ( start != sentinel ) {
9915 if ( cmp( *start, value ) ) { break; }
9916 ++start;
9917 }
9918 return start;
9919 }
9920
9921 template <typename ForwardIter,
9922 typename Sentinel,
9923 typename T,
9924 typename Comparator>
9925 constexpr
9926 std::ptrdiff_t count_sentinel( ForwardIter start,
9927 Sentinel sentinel,
9928 T const& value,
9929 Comparator cmp ) {
9930 std::ptrdiff_t count = 0;
9931 while ( start != sentinel ) {
9932 if ( cmp( *start, value ) ) { ++count; }
9933 ++start;
9934 }
9935 return count;
9936 }
9937
9938 template <typename ForwardIter, typename Sentinel>
9939 constexpr
9940 std::enable_if_t<!std::is_same<ForwardIter, Sentinel>::value,
9941 std::ptrdiff_t>
9942 sentinel_distance( ForwardIter iter, const Sentinel sentinel ) {
9943 std::ptrdiff_t dist = 0;
9944 while ( iter != sentinel ) {
9945 ++iter;
9946 ++dist;
9947 }
9948 return dist;
9949 }
9950
9951 template <typename ForwardIter>
9952 constexpr std::ptrdiff_t sentinel_distance( ForwardIter first,
9953 ForwardIter last ) {
9954 return std::distance( first, last );
9955 }
9956
9957 template <typename ForwardIter1,
9958 typename Sentinel1,
9959 typename ForwardIter2,
9960 typename Sentinel2,
9961 typename Comparator>
9962 constexpr bool check_element_counts( ForwardIter1 first_1,
9963 const Sentinel1 end_1,
9964 ForwardIter2 first_2,
9965 const Sentinel2 end_2,
9966 Comparator cmp ) {
9967 auto cursor = first_1;
9968 while ( cursor != end_1 ) {
9969 if ( find_sentinel( first_1, cursor, *cursor, cmp ) ==
9970 cursor ) {
9971 // we haven't checked this element yet
9972 const auto count_in_range_2 =
9973 count_sentinel( first_2, end_2, *cursor, cmp );
9974 // Not a single instance in 2nd range, so it cannot be a
9975 // permutation of 1st range
9976 if ( count_in_range_2 == 0 ) { return false; }
9977
9978 const auto count_in_range_1 =
9979 count_sentinel( cursor, end_1, *cursor, cmp );
9980 if ( count_in_range_1 != count_in_range_2 ) {
9981 return false;
9982 }
9983 }
9984
9985 ++cursor;
9986 }
9987
9988 return true;
9989 }
9990
9991 template <typename ForwardIter1,
9992 typename Sentinel1,
9993 typename ForwardIter2,
9994 typename Sentinel2,
9995 typename Comparator>
9996 constexpr bool is_permutation( ForwardIter1 first_1,
9997 const Sentinel1 end_1,
9998 ForwardIter2 first_2,
9999 const Sentinel2 end_2,
10000 Comparator cmp ) {
10001 // TODO: no optimization for stronger iterators, because we would also have to constrain on sentinel vs not sentinel types
10002 // TODO: Comparator has to be "both sides", e.g. a == b => b == a
10003 // This skips shared prefix of the two ranges
10004 while (first_1 != end_1 && first_2 != end_2 && cmp(*first_1, *first_2)) {
10005 ++first_1;
10006 ++first_2;
10007 }
10008
10009 // We need to handle case where at least one of the ranges has no more elements
10010 if (first_1 == end_1 || first_2 == end_2) {
10011 return first_1 == end_1 && first_2 == end_2;
10012 }
10013
10014 // pair counting is n**2, so we pay linear walk to compare the sizes first
10015 auto dist_1 = sentinel_distance( first_1, end_1 );
10016 auto dist_2 = sentinel_distance( first_2, end_2 );
10017
10018 if (dist_1 != dist_2) { return false; }
10019
10020 // Since we do not try to handle stronger iterators pair (e.g.
10021 // bidir) optimally, the only thing left to do is to check counts in
10022 // the remaining ranges.
10023 return check_element_counts( first_1, end_1, first_2, end_2, cmp );
10024 }
10025
10026 } // namespace Detail
10027} // namespace Catch
10028
10029#endif // CATCH_IS_PERMUTATION_HPP_INCLUDED
10030
10031

10095 class JsonValueWriter {

10103 template <typename T>
10104 void write( T const& value ) && {
10105 writeImpl( value, !std::is_arithmetic<T>::value );
10106 }
10107 void write( StringRef value ) &&;
10108 void write( bool value ) &&;
10109
10110 private:
10111 void writeImpl( StringRef value, bool quote );
10112
10113 // Without this SFINAE, this overload is a better match
10114 // for `std::string`, `char const*`, `char const[N]` args.
10115 // While it would still work, it would cause code bloat
10116 // and multiple iteration over the strings
10117 template <typename T,
10118 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
10119 !std::is_convertible<T, StringRef>::value>>
10120 void writeImpl( T const& value, bool quote_value ) {
10121 m_sstream << value;
10122 writeImpl( m_sstream.str(), quote_value );
10123 }
10124
10125 std::ostream& m_os;
10126 std::stringstream m_sstream;
10127 std::uint64_t m_indent_level;
10128 };

10146 bool m_active = true;
10147 };

10160 JsonArrayWriter writeArray();
10161
10162 template <typename T>
10163 JsonArrayWriter& write( T const& value ) {
10164 return writeImpl( value );
10165 }
10166
10167 JsonArrayWriter& write( bool value );
10168
10169 private:
10170 template <typename T>
10171 JsonArrayWriter& writeImpl( T const& value ) {
10172 JsonUtils::appendCommaNewline(
10173 m_os, m_should_comma, m_indent_level + 1 );
10174 JsonValueWriter{ m_os }.write( value );
10175
10176 return *this;
10177 }
10178
10179 std::ostream& m_os;
10180 std::uint64_t m_indent_level;
10181 bool m_should_comma = false;
10182 bool m_active = true;
10183 };
10184
10185} // namespace Catch
10186
10187#endif // CATCH_JSONWRITER_HPP_INCLUDED

10395 struct NameAndLocation {
10396 std::string name;
10397 SourceLineInfo location;
10398
10399 NameAndLocation( std::string&& _name, SourceLineInfo const& _location );
10400 friend bool operator==(NameAndLocation const& lhs, NameAndLocation const& rhs) {
10401 // This is a very cheap check that should have a very high hit rate.
10402 // If we get to SourceLineInfo::operator==, we will redo it, but the
10403 // cost of repeating is trivial at that point (we will be paying
10404 // multiple strcmp/memcmps at that point).
10405 if ( lhs.location.line != rhs.location.line ) { return false; }
10406 return lhs.name == rhs.name && lhs.location == rhs.location;
10407 }
10408 friend bool operator!=(NameAndLocation const& lhs,
10409 NameAndLocation const& rhs) {
10410 return !( lhs == rhs );
10411 }
10412 };
10413
10421 struct NameAndLocationRef {
10422 StringRef name;
10423 SourceLineInfo location;
10424
10425 constexpr NameAndLocationRef( StringRef name_,
10426 SourceLineInfo location_ ):
10427 name( name_ ), location( location_ ) {}
10428
10429 friend bool operator==( NameAndLocation const& lhs,
10430 NameAndLocationRef const& rhs ) {
10431 // This is a very cheap check that should have a very high hit rate.
10432 // If we get to SourceLineInfo::operator==, we will redo it, but the
10433 // cost of repeating is trivial at that point (we will be paying
10434 // multiple strcmp/memcmps at that point).
10435 if ( lhs.location.line != rhs.location.line ) { return false; }
10436 return StringRef( lhs.name ) == rhs.name &&
10437 lhs.location == rhs.location;
10438 }
10439 friend bool operator==( NameAndLocationRef const& lhs,
10440 NameAndLocation const& rhs ) {
10441 return rhs == lhs;
10442 }
10443 };
10444

10807#ifndef CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
10808#define CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
10809
10810#include <cassert>
10811#include <algorithm>
10812
10813namespace Catch {
10814
10815 template<typename Container>
10816 Container createShard(Container const& container, std::size_t const shardCount, std::size_t const shardIndex) {
10817 assert(shardCount > shardIndex);
10818
10819 if (shardCount == 1) {
10820 return container;
10821 }
10822
10823 const std::size_t totalTestCount = container.size();
10824
10825 const std::size_t shardSize = totalTestCount / shardCount;
10826 const std::size_t leftoverTests = totalTestCount % shardCount;
10827
10828 const std::size_t startIndex = shardIndex * shardSize + (std::min)(shardIndex, leftoverTests);
10829 const std::size_t endIndex = (shardIndex + 1) * shardSize + (std::min)(shardIndex + 1, leftoverTests);
10830
10831 auto startIterator = std::next(container.begin(), static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(startIndex));
10832 auto endIterator = std::next(container.begin(), static_cast<std::ptrdiff_t>(endIndex));
10833
10834 return Container(startIterator, endIterator);
10835 }
10836
10837}
10838
10839#endif // CATCH_SHARDING_HPP_INCLUDED
10840

10842#ifndef CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED
10843#define CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED
10844
10845namespace Catch {
10846
10847 struct ISingleton {
10848 virtual ~ISingleton(); // = default
10849 };
10850
10851
10852 void addSingleton( ISingleton* singleton );
10853 void cleanupSingletons();
10854
10855
10856 template<typename SingletonImplT, typename InterfaceT = SingletonImplT, typename MutableInterfaceT = InterfaceT>
10857 class Singleton : SingletonImplT, public ISingleton {
10858
10859 static auto getInternal() -> Singleton* {
10860 static Singleton* s_instance = nullptr;
10861 if( !s_instance ) {
10862 s_instance = new Singleton;
10863 addSingleton( s_instance );
10864 }
10865 return s_instance;
10866 }
10867
10868 public:
10869 static auto get() -> InterfaceT const& {
10870 return *getInternal();
10871 }
10872 static auto getMutable() -> MutableInterfaceT& {
10873 return *getInternal();
10874 }
10875 };
10876
10877} // namespace Catch

10879#endif // CATCH_SINGLETONS_HPP_INCLUDED

11179 class AnsiSkippingString {
11180 std::string m_string;
11181 std::size_t m_size = 0;
11182
11183 // perform 0xff replacement and calculate m_size
11184 void preprocessString();
11185
11186 public:
11187 class const_iterator;
11188 using iterator = const_iterator;
11189 // note: must be u-suffixed or this will cause a "truncation of
11190 // constant value" warning on MSVC
11191 static constexpr char sentinel = static_cast<char>( 0xffu );
11192
11193 explicit AnsiSkippingString( std::string const& text );
11194 explicit AnsiSkippingString( std::string&& text );
11195
11196 const_iterator begin() const;
11197 const_iterator end() const;
11198
11199 size_t size() const { return m_size; }
11200
11201 std::string substring( const_iterator begin,
11202 const_iterator end ) const;
11203 };
11204
11205 class AnsiSkippingString::const_iterator {
11206 friend AnsiSkippingString;
11207 struct EndTag {};
11208
11209 const std::string* m_string;
11210 std::string::const_iterator m_it;
11211
11212 explicit const_iterator( const std::string& string, EndTag ):
11213 m_string( &string ), m_it( string.end() ) {}
11214
11215 void tryParseAnsiEscapes();
11216 void advance();
11217 void unadvance();
11218
11219 public:
11220 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
11221 using value_type = char;
11222 using pointer = value_type*;
11223 using reference = value_type&;
11224 using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
11225
11226 explicit const_iterator( const std::string& string ):
11227 m_string( &string ), m_it( string.begin() ) {
11228 tryParseAnsiEscapes();
11229 }
11230
11231 char operator*() const { return *m_it; }
11232
11233 const_iterator& operator++() {
11234 advance();
11235 return *this;
11236 }
11237 const_iterator operator++( int ) {
11238 iterator prev( *this );
11239 operator++();
11240 return prev;
11241 }
11242 const_iterator& operator--() {
11243 unadvance();
11244 return *this;
11245 }
11246 const_iterator operator--( int ) {
11247 iterator prev( *this );
11248 operator--();
11249 return prev;
11250 }
11251
11252 bool operator==( const_iterator const& other ) const {
11253 return m_it == other.m_it;
11254 }
11255 bool operator!=( const_iterator const& other ) const {
11256 return !operator==( other );
11257 }
11258 bool operator<=( const_iterator const& other ) const {
11259 return m_it <= other.m_it;
11260 }
11261
11262 const_iterator oneBefore() const {
11263 auto it = *this;
11264 return --it;
11265 }
11266 };

11275 class Column {
11276 // String to be written out
11277 AnsiSkippingString m_string;
11278 // Width of the column for linebreaking
11279 size_t m_width = CATCH_CONFIG_CONSOLE_WIDTH - 1;
11280 // Indentation of other lines (including first if initial indent is
11281 // unset)
11282 size_t m_indent = 0;
11283 // Indentation of the first line
11284 size_t m_initialIndent = std::string::npos;
11285
11286 public:
11290 class const_iterator {
11291 friend Column;
11292 struct EndTag {};
11293
11294 Column const& m_column;
11295 // Where does the current line start?
11296 AnsiSkippingString::const_iterator m_lineStart;
11297 // How long should the current line be?
11298 AnsiSkippingString::const_iterator m_lineEnd;
11299 // How far have we checked the string to iterate?
11300 AnsiSkippingString::const_iterator m_parsedTo;
11301 // Should a '-' be appended to the line?
11302 bool m_addHyphen = false;
11303
11304 const_iterator( Column const& column, EndTag ):
11305 m_column( column ),
11306 m_lineStart( m_column.m_string.end() ),
11307 m_lineEnd( column.m_string.end() ),
11308 m_parsedTo( column.m_string.end() ) {}
11309
11310 // Calculates the length of the current line
11311 void calcLength();
11312
11313 // Returns current indentation width
11314 size_t indentSize() const;
11315
11316 // Creates an indented and (optionally) suffixed string from
11317 // current iterator position, indentation and length.
11318 std::string addIndentAndSuffix(
11319 AnsiSkippingString::const_iterator start,
11320 AnsiSkippingString::const_iterator end ) const;
11321
11322 public:
11323 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
11324 using value_type = std::string;
11325 using pointer = value_type*;
11326 using reference = value_type&;
11327 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
11328
11329 explicit const_iterator( Column const& column );
11330
11331 std::string operator*() const;
11332
11333 const_iterator& operator++();
11334 const_iterator operator++( int );
11335
11336 bool operator==( const_iterator const& other ) const {
11337 return m_lineStart == other.m_lineStart &&
11338 &m_column == &other.m_column;
11339 }
11340 bool operator!=( const_iterator const& other ) const {
11341 return !operator==( other );
11342 }
11343 };
11344 using iterator = const_iterator;
11345
11346 explicit Column( std::string const& text ): m_string( text ) {}
11347 explicit Column( std::string&& text ):
11348 m_string( CATCH_MOVE( text ) ) {}
11349
11350 Column& width( size_t newWidth ) & {
11351 assert( newWidth > 0 );
11352 m_width = newWidth;
11353 return *this;
11354 }
11355 Column&& width( size_t newWidth ) && {
11356 assert( newWidth > 0 );
11357 m_width = newWidth;
11358 return CATCH_MOVE( *this );
11359 }
11360 Column& indent( size_t newIndent ) & {
11361 m_indent = newIndent;
11362 return *this;
11363 }
11364 Column&& indent( size_t newIndent ) && {
11365 m_indent = newIndent;
11366 return CATCH_MOVE( *this );
11367 }
11368 Column& initialIndent( size_t newIndent ) & {
11369 m_initialIndent = newIndent;
11370 return *this;
11371 }
11372 Column&& initialIndent( size_t newIndent ) && {
11373 m_initialIndent = newIndent;
11374 return CATCH_MOVE( *this );
11375 }
11376
11377 size_t width() const { return m_width; }
11378 const_iterator begin() const { return const_iterator( *this ); }
11379 const_iterator end() const {
11380 return { *this, const_iterator::EndTag{} };
11381 }
11382
11383 friend std::ostream& operator<<( std::ostream& os,
11384 Column const& col );
11385
11386 friend Columns operator+( Column const& lhs, Column const& rhs );
11387 friend Columns operator+( Column&& lhs, Column&& rhs );
11388 };

11486 enum class XmlFormatting : std::uint8_t {
11487 None = 0x00,
11488 Indent = 0x01,
11489 Newline = 0x02,
11490 };
11491
11492 constexpr XmlFormatting operator|( XmlFormatting lhs, XmlFormatting rhs ) {
11493 return static_cast<XmlFormatting>( static_cast<std::uint8_t>( lhs ) |
11494 static_cast<std::uint8_t>( rhs ) );
11495 }
11496
11497 constexpr XmlFormatting operator&( XmlFormatting lhs, XmlFormatting rhs ) {
11498 return static_cast<XmlFormatting>( static_cast<std::uint8_t>( lhs ) &
11499 static_cast<std::uint8_t>( rhs ) );
11500 }

11545 template <typename T,
11546 // Without this SFINAE, this overload is a better match
11547 // for `std::string`, `char const*`, `char const[N]` args.
11548 // While it would still work, it would cause code bloat
11549 // and multiple iteration over the strings
11550 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
11551 !std::is_convertible<T, StringRef>::value>>
11552 ScopedElement& writeAttribute( StringRef name,
11553 T const& attribute ) {
11554 m_writer->writeAttribute( name, attribute );
11555 return *this;
11556 }
11557

11583
11586 template <typename T,
11587 // Without this SFINAE, this overload is a better match
11588 // for `std::string`, `char const*`, `char const[N]` args.
11589 // While it would still work, it would cause code bloat
11590 // and multiple iteration over the strings
11591 typename = typename std::enable_if_t<
11592 !std::is_convertible<T, StringRef>::value>>
11593 XmlWriter& writeAttribute( StringRef name, T const& attribute ) {
11594 ReusableStringStream rss;
11595 rss << attribute;

11673 template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
11674 class MatchExpr : public ITransientExpression {
11675 ArgT && m_arg;
11676 MatcherT const& m_matcher;
11677 public:
11678 constexpr MatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher )
11679 : ITransientExpression{ true, matcher.match( arg ) }, // not forwarding arg here on purpose
11680 m_arg( CATCH_FORWARD(arg) ),
11681 m_matcher( matcher )
11682 {}
11683
11684 void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream& os ) const override {
11685 os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_arg )
11686 << ' '
11687 << m_matcher.toString();
11688 }
11689 };

11692# pragma clang diagnostic pop
11693#elif defined __GNUC__
11694# pragma GCC diagnostic pop
11695#endif

11698 namespace Matchers {
11699 template <typename ArgT>
11700 class MatcherBase;
11701 }
11702
11703 using StringMatcher = Matchers::MatcherBase<std::string>;
11704
11705 void handleExceptionMatchExpr( AssertionHandler& handler, StringMatcher const& matcher );
11706
11707 template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
11708 constexpr MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT>
11709 makeMatchExpr( ArgT&& arg, MatcherT const& matcher ) {
11710 return MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT>( CATCH_FORWARD(arg), matcher );
11711 }
11712
11713} // namespace Catch

11715
11717#define INTERNAL_CHECK_THAT( macroName, matcher, resultDisposition, arg ) \
11718 do { \
11719 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(arg) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
11720 INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
11721 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( arg, matcher ) ); \
11722 } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
11723 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
11724 } while( false )
11725
11726
11728#define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_MATCHES( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
11729 do { \
11730 Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
11731 if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
11732 try { \
11733 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
11734 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_USELESS_CAST_WARNINGS \
11735 static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__ ); \
11736 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
11737 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
11738 } \
11739 catch( exceptionType const& ex ) { \
11740 catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( ex, matcher ) ); \
11741 } \
11742 catch( ... ) { \
11743 catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
11744 } \
11745 else \
11746 catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
11747 catchAssertionHandler.complete(); \
11748 } while( false )
11749

11751#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_IMPL_HPP_INCLUDED

11778 template<typename T>
11779 class MatcherBase : public MatcherUntypedBase {
11780 public:
11781 virtual bool match( T const& arg ) const = 0;
11782 };

11784 namespace Detail {
11785
11786 template<typename ArgT>
11787 class MatchAllOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
11788 std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
11789
11790 public:
11791 MatchAllOf() = default;
11792 MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
11793 MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
11794 MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
11795 MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
11796
11797
11798 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
11799 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
11800 if (!matcher->match(arg))
11801 return false;
11802 }
11803 return true;
11804 }
11805 std::string describe() const override {
11806 std::string description;
11807 description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
11808 description += "( ";
11809 bool first = true;
11810 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
11811 if( first )
11812 first = false;
11813 else
11814 description += " and ";
11815 description += matcher->toString();
11816 }
11817 description += " )";
11818 return description;
11819 }
11820
11821 friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatchAllOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
11822 lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
11823 return CATCH_MOVE(lhs);
11824 }
11825 friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf&& rhs) {
11826 rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
11827 return CATCH_MOVE(rhs);
11828 }
11829 };
11830
11833 template<typename ArgT>
11834 MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
11837 template<typename ArgT>
11838 MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
11839
11840 template<typename ArgT>
11841 class MatchAnyOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
11842 std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
11843 public:
11844 MatchAnyOf() = default;
11845 MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
11846 MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
11847 MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
11848 MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
11849
11850 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
11851 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
11852 if (matcher->match(arg))
11853 return true;
11854 }
11855 return false;
11856 }
11857 std::string describe() const override {
11858 std::string description;
11859 description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
11860 description += "( ";
11861 bool first = true;
11862 for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
11863 if( first )
11864 first = false;
11865 else
11866 description += " or ";
11867 description += matcher->toString();
11868 }
11869 description += " )";
11870 return description;
11871 }
11872
11873 friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatchAnyOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
11874 lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
11875 return CATCH_MOVE(lhs);
11876 }
11877 friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf&& rhs) {
11878 rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
11879 return CATCH_MOVE(rhs);
11880 }
11881 };
11882
11885 template<typename ArgT>
11886 MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
11889 template<typename ArgT>
11890 MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
11891
11892 template<typename ArgT>
11893 class MatchNotOf final : public MatcherBase<ArgT> {
11894 MatcherBase<ArgT> const& m_underlyingMatcher;
11895
11896 public:
11897 explicit MatchNotOf( MatcherBase<ArgT> const& underlyingMatcher ):
11898 m_underlyingMatcher( underlyingMatcher )
11899 {}
11900
11901 bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
11902 return !m_underlyingMatcher.match( arg );
11903 }
11904
11905 std::string describe() const override {
11906 return "not " + m_underlyingMatcher.toString();
11907 }
11908 };
11909
11910 } // namespace Detail
11911
11912 template <typename T>
11913 Detail::MatchAllOf<T> operator&& (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
11914 return Detail::MatchAllOf<T>{} && lhs && rhs;
11915 }
11916 template <typename T>
11917 Detail::MatchAnyOf<T> operator|| (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
11918 return Detail::MatchAnyOf<T>{} || lhs || rhs;
11919 }
11920
11921 template <typename T>
11922 Detail::MatchNotOf<T> operator! (MatcherBase<T> const& matcher) {
11923 return Detail::MatchNotOf<T>{ matcher };
11924 }

11995 class MatcherGenericBase : public MatcherUntypedBase {
11996 public:

11998 ~MatcherGenericBase() override; // = default;

12009 template<std::size_t N, std::size_t M>
12010 std::array<void const*, N + M> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, std::array<void const*, M> && rhs) {
12011 std::array<void const*, N + M> arr{};
12012 std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
12013 std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), M, arr.begin() + N);
12014 return arr;
12015 }
12016
12017 template<std::size_t N>
12018 std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, void const* rhs) {
12019 std::array<void const*, N+1> arr{};
12020 std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
12021 arr[N] = rhs;
12022 return arr;
12023 }
12024
12025 template<std::size_t N>
12026 std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(void const* lhs, std::array<void const*, N> && rhs) {
12027 std::array<void const*, N + 1> arr{ {lhs} };
12028 std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), N, arr.begin() + 1);
12029 return arr;
12030 }
12031
12032 template<typename T>
12033 static constexpr bool is_generic_matcher_v = std::is_base_of<
12034 Catch::Matchers::MatcherGenericBase,
12035 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
12036 >::value;
12037
12038 template<typename... Ts>
12039 static constexpr bool are_generic_matchers_v = Catch::Detail::conjunction<std::integral_constant<bool,is_generic_matcher_v<Ts>>...>::value;
12040
12041 template<typename T>
12042 static constexpr bool is_matcher_v = std::is_base_of<
12043 Catch::Matchers::MatcherUntypedBase,
12044 std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
12045 >::value;
12046
12047
12048 template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
12049 bool match_all_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
12050 return true;
12051 }
12052
12053 template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
12054 bool match_all_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
12055 return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) && match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
12056 }
12057
12058
12059 template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
12060 bool match_any_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
12061 return false;
12062 }
12063
12064 template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
12065 bool match_any_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
12066 return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) || match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
12067 }
12068
12069 std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::string const* descriptions_begin, std::string const* descriptions_end);
12070
12071 template<typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t... Idx>
12072 std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx...>) {
12073 std::array<std::string, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> descriptions {{
12074 static_cast<MatcherTs const*>(matchers[Idx])->toString()...
12075 }};
12076
12077 return describe_multi_matcher(combine, descriptions.data(), descriptions.data() + descriptions.size());
12078 }

12081 template<typename... MatcherTs>
12082 class MatchAllOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12083 public:
12084 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
12085 MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
12086 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
12087 MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
12088
12089 MatchAllOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
12090 explicit MatchAllOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
12091
12092 template<typename Arg>
12093 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
12094 return match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
12095 }
12096
12097 std::string describe() const override {
12098 return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" and "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
12099 }
12100
12101 // Has to be public to enable the concatenating operators
12102 // below, because they are not friend of the RHS, only LHS,
12103 // and thus cannot access private fields of RHS
12104 std::array<void const*, sizeof...( MatcherTs )> m_matchers;
12105
12106
12108 template<typename... MatchersRHS>
12109 friend
12110 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator && (
12111 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
12112 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
12113 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
12114 }
12115
12117 template<typename MatcherRHS>
12118 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher_v<MatcherRHS>,
12119 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator && (
12120 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
12121 MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
12122 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(&rhs))};
12123 }
12124
12126 template<typename MatcherLHS>
12127 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher_v<MatcherLHS>,
12128 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>> operator && (
12129 MatcherLHS const& lhs,
12130 MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& rhs) {
12131 return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>{array_cat(static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(lhs)), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
12132 }
12133 };
12134

12136 template<typename... MatcherTs>
12137 class MatchAnyOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12138 public:
12139 MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatchAnyOfGeneric const&) = delete;
12140 MatchAnyOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAnyOfGeneric const&) = delete;
12141 MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatchAnyOfGeneric&&) = default;
12142 MatchAnyOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAnyOfGeneric&&) = default;
12143
12144 MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
12145 explicit MatchAnyOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
12146
12147 template<typename Arg>
12148 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
12149 return match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
12150 }
12151
12152 std::string describe() const override {
12153 return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" or "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
12154 }
12155
12156
12157 // Has to be public to enable the concatenating operators
12158 // below, because they are not friend of the RHS, only LHS,
12159 // and thus cannot access private fields of RHS
12160 std::array<void const*, sizeof...( MatcherTs )> m_matchers;
12161
12163 template<typename... MatchersRHS>
12164 friend MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator || (
12165 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
12166 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
12167 return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), CATCH_MOVE(rhs.m_matchers))};
12168 }
12169
12171 template<typename MatcherRHS>
12172 friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher_v<MatcherRHS>,
12173 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator || (
12174 MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
12175 MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
12176 return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(CATCH_MOVE(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(rhs)))};
12177 }

12186 }

12191 class MatchNotOfGeneric final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12192 MatcherT const& m_matcher;
12193
12194 public:
12195 MatchNotOfGeneric(MatchNotOfGeneric const&) = delete;
12196 MatchNotOfGeneric& operator=(MatchNotOfGeneric const&) = delete;
12197 MatchNotOfGeneric(MatchNotOfGeneric&&) = default;

12199

12203 bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
12204 return !m_matcher.match(arg);
12205 }

12208 return "not " + m_matcher.toString();
12209 }
12210

12213 return matcher.m_matcher;
12214 }

12221 std::enable_if_t<Detail::are_generic_matchers_v<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>, Detail::MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherRHS>>
12222 operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
12223 return { lhs, rhs };
12224 }

12228 operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
12229 return { lhs, rhs };
12230 }

12235 operator ! (MatcherT const& matcher) {
12236 return Detail::MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT>{matcher};

12244 return { lhs, rhs };
12245 }

12249 operator && (MatcherBase<ArgLHS> const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
12250 return { lhs, rhs };

12255 operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgRHS> const& rhs) {
12256 return { lhs, rhs };

12261 operator || (MatcherBase<ArgLHS> const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
12262 return { lhs, rhs };

12273 class IsEmptyMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12274 public:
12275 template <typename RangeLike>
12276 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
12277#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
12278 using Catch::Detail::empty;
12279#else
12280 using std::empty;
12281#endif
12282 return empty(rng);
12283 }
12284
12285 std::string describe() const override;
12286 };

12288 class HasSizeMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12289 std::size_t m_target_size;
12290 public:
12291 explicit HasSizeMatcher(std::size_t target_size):
12292 m_target_size(target_size)
12293 {}
12294
12295 template <typename RangeLike>
12296 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
12297#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
12298 using Catch::Detail::size;
12299#else
12300 using std::size;
12301#endif
12302 return size(rng) == m_target_size;
12303 }
12304
12305 std::string describe() const override;
12306 };
12307
12308 template <typename Matcher>
12309 class SizeMatchesMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12310 Matcher m_matcher;
12311 public:
12312 explicit SizeMatchesMatcher(Matcher m):
12313 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(m))
12314 {}
12315
12316 template <typename RangeLike>
12317 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
12318#if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
12319 using Catch::Detail::size;
12320#else
12321 using std::size;
12322#endif
12323 return m_matcher.match(size(rng));
12324 }
12325
12326 std::string describe() const override {
12327 return "size matches " + m_matcher.describe();
12328 }
12329 };
12330
12331
12333 IsEmptyMatcher IsEmpty();
12335 HasSizeMatcher SizeIs(std::size_t sz);
12336 template <typename Matcher>
12337 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_matcher_v<Matcher>,
12338 SizeMatchesMatcher<Matcher>> SizeIs(Matcher&& m) {
12339 return SizeMatchesMatcher<Matcher>{CATCH_FORWARD(m)};
12340 }

12358 template <typename T, typename Equality>
12359 class ContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12360 T m_desired;
12361 Equality m_eq;
12362 public:
12363 template <typename T2, typename Equality2>
12364 ContainsElementMatcher(T2&& target, Equality2&& predicate):
12365 m_desired(CATCH_FORWARD(target)),
12366 m_eq(CATCH_FORWARD(predicate))
12367 {}
12368
12369 std::string describe() const override {
12370 return "contains element " + Catch::Detail::stringify(m_desired);
12371 }
12372
12373 template <typename RangeLike>
12374 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
12375 for ( auto&& elem : rng ) {
12376 if ( m_eq( elem, m_desired ) ) { return true; }
12377 }
12378 return false;
12379 }
12380 };
12381
12383 template <typename Matcher>
12384 class ContainsMatcherMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12385 Matcher m_matcher;
12386 public:
12387 // Note that we do a copy+move to avoid having to SFINAE this
12388 // constructor (and also avoid some perfect forwarding failure
12389 // cases)
12390 ContainsMatcherMatcher(Matcher matcher):
12391 m_matcher(CATCH_MOVE(matcher))
12392 {}
12393
12394 template <typename RangeLike>
12395 bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
12396 for (auto&& elem : rng) {
12397 if (m_matcher.match(elem)) {
12398 return true;
12399 }
12400 }
12401 return false;
12402 }
12403
12404 std::string describe() const override {
12405 return "contains element matching " + m_matcher.describe();
12406 }
12407 };
12408
12414 template <typename T>
12415 std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_matcher_v<T>,
12416 ContainsElementMatcher<T, std::equal_to<>>> Contains(T&& elem) {
12417 return { CATCH_FORWARD(elem), std::equal_to<>{} };
12418 }
12419
12421 template <typename Matcher>
12422 std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_matcher_v<Matcher>,
12423 ContainsMatcherMatcher<Matcher>> Contains(Matcher&& matcher) {
12424 return { CATCH_FORWARD(matcher) };
12425 }
12426
12432 template <typename T, typename Equality>
12433 ContainsElementMatcher<T, Equality> Contains(T&& elem, Equality&& eq) {
12434 return { CATCH_FORWARD(elem), CATCH_FORWARD(eq) };
12435 }
12436
12437 }
12438}

12544 // Given IEEE-754 format for floats and doubles, we can assume
12545 // that float -> double promotion is lossless. Given this, we can
12546 // assume that if we do the standard relative comparison of
12547 // |lhs - rhs| <= epsilon * max(fabs(lhs), fabs(rhs)), then we get
12548 // the same result if we do this for floats, as if we do this for
12549 // doubles that were promoted from floats.
12550 class WithinRelMatcher final : public MatcherBase<double> {
12551 public:
12552 WithinRelMatcher( double target, double epsilon );
12553 bool match(double const& matchee) const override;
12554 std::string describe() const override;
12555 private:
12556 double m_target;
12557 double m_epsilon;
12558 };
12559
12561 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target, double eps);
12563 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target);
12565 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target, float eps);
12567 WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target);
12568

12625 PredicateMatcher<T, Pred> Predicate(Pred&& predicate, std::string const& description = "") {
12626 static_assert(is_callable<Pred(T)>::value, "Predicate not callable with argument T");
12627 static_assert(std::is_same<bool, FunctionReturnType<Pred, T>>::value, "Predicate does not return bool");

12795#ifndef CATCH_MATCHERS_RANGE_EQUALS_HPP_INCLUDED

12798
12799#include <functional>
12800
12801namespace Catch {
12802 namespace Matchers {
12803
12808 template <typename TargetRangeLike, typename Equality>
12809 class RangeEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12810 TargetRangeLike m_desired;
12811 Equality m_predicate;
12812
12813 public:
12814 template <typename TargetRangeLike2, typename Equality2>
12815 constexpr
12816 RangeEqualsMatcher( TargetRangeLike2&& range,
12817 Equality2&& predicate ):
12818 m_desired( CATCH_FORWARD( range ) ),
12819 m_predicate( CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) ) {}
12820
12821 template <typename RangeLike>
12822 constexpr
12823 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
12824 auto rng_start = begin( rng );
12825 const auto rng_end = end( rng );
12826 auto target_start = begin( m_desired );
12827 const auto target_end = end( m_desired );
12828
12829 while (rng_start != rng_end && target_start != target_end) {
12830 if (!m_predicate(*rng_start, *target_start)) {
12831 return false;
12832 }
12833 ++rng_start;
12834 ++target_start;
12835 }
12836 return rng_start == rng_end && target_start == target_end;
12837 }
12838
12839 std::string describe() const override {
12840 return "elements are " + Catch::Detail::stringify( m_desired );
12841 }
12842 };
12843
12848 template <typename TargetRangeLike, typename Equality>
12849 class UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
12850 TargetRangeLike m_desired;
12851 Equality m_predicate;
12852
12853 public:
12854 template <typename TargetRangeLike2, typename Equality2>
12855 constexpr
12856 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher( TargetRangeLike2&& range,
12857 Equality2&& predicate ):
12858 m_desired( CATCH_FORWARD( range ) ),
12859 m_predicate( CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) ) {}
12860
12861 template <typename RangeLike>
12862 constexpr
12863 bool match( RangeLike&& rng ) const {
12864 using std::begin;
12865 using std::end;
12866 return Catch::Detail::is_permutation( begin( m_desired ),
12867 end( m_desired ),
12868 begin( rng ),
12869 end( rng ),
12870 m_predicate );
12871 }
12872
12873 std::string describe() const override {
12874 return "unordered elements are " +
12875 ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_desired );
12876 }
12877 };
12878
12886 template <typename RangeLike,
12887 typename Equality = decltype( std::equal_to<>{} )>
12888 constexpr
12889 RangeEqualsMatcher<RangeLike, Equality>
12890 RangeEquals( RangeLike&& range,
12891 Equality&& predicate = std::equal_to<>{} ) {
12892 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) };
12893 }
12894
12902 template <typename T,
12903 typename Equality = decltype( std::equal_to<>{} )>
12904 constexpr
12905 RangeEqualsMatcher<std::initializer_list<T>, Equality>
12906 RangeEquals( std::initializer_list<T> range,
12907 Equality&& predicate = std::equal_to<>{} ) {
12908 return { range, CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) };
12909 }
12910
12918 template <typename RangeLike,
12919 typename Equality = decltype( std::equal_to<>{} )>
12920 constexpr
12921 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher<RangeLike, Equality>
12922 UnorderedRangeEquals( RangeLike&& range,
12923 Equality&& predicate = std::equal_to<>{} ) {
12924 return { CATCH_FORWARD( range ), CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) };
12925 }
12926
12934 template <typename T,
12935 typename Equality = decltype( std::equal_to<>{} )>
12936 constexpr
12937 UnorderedRangeEqualsMatcher<std::initializer_list<T>, Equality>
12938 UnorderedRangeEquals( std::initializer_list<T> range,
12939 Equality&& predicate = std::equal_to<>{} ) {
12940 return { range, CATCH_FORWARD( predicate ) };
12941 }

13034 template<typename T, typename Alloc>
13035 class VectorContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, Alloc>> {
13036 T const& m_comparator;
13037
13038 public:
13039 VectorContainsElementMatcher(T const& comparator):
13040 m_comparator(comparator)
13041 {}
13042
13043 bool match(std::vector<T, Alloc> const& v) const override {
13044 for (auto const& el : v) {
13045 if (el == m_comparator) {
13046 return true;
13047 }
13048 }
13049 return false;
13050 }
13051
13052 std::string describe() const override {
13053 return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
13054 }
13055 };
13056
13057 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
13058 class ContainsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
13059 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
13060
13061 public:
13062 ContainsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
13063 m_comparator( comparator )
13064 {}
13065
13066 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
13067 // !TBD: see note in EqualsMatcher
13068 if (m_comparator.size() > v.size())
13069 return false;
13070 for (auto const& comparator : m_comparator) {
13071 auto present = false;
13072 for (const auto& el : v) {
13073 if (el == comparator) {
13074 present = true;
13075 break;
13076 }
13077 }
13078 if (!present) {
13079 return false;
13080 }
13081 }
13082 return true;
13083 }
13084 std::string describe() const override {
13085 return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
13086 }
13087 };
13088
13089 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
13090 class EqualsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
13091 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
13092
13093 public:
13094 EqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
13095 m_comparator( comparator )
13096 {}
13097
13098 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
13099 // !TBD: This currently works if all elements can be compared using !=
13100 // - a more general approach would be via a compare template that defaults
13101 // to using !=. but could be specialised for, e.g. std::vector<T> etc
13102 // - then just call that directly
13103 if ( m_comparator.size() != v.size() ) { return false; }
13104 for ( std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i ) {
13105 if ( !( m_comparator[i] == v[i] ) ) { return false; }
13106 }
13107 return true;
13108 }
13109 std::string describe() const override {
13110 return "Equals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
13111 }
13112 };
13113
13114 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
13115 class ApproxMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
13116 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
13117 mutable Catch::Approx approx = Catch::Approx::custom();
13118
13119 public:
13120 ApproxMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
13121 m_comparator( comparator )
13122 {}
13123
13124 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
13125 if (m_comparator.size() != v.size())
13126 return false;
13127 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i)
13128 if (m_comparator[i] != approx(v[i]))
13129 return false;
13130 return true;
13131 }
13132 std::string describe() const override {
13133 return "is approx: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
13134 }
13135 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
13136 ApproxMatcher& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
13137 approx.epsilon(static_cast<double>(newEpsilon));
13138 return *this;
13139 }
13140 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
13141 ApproxMatcher& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
13142 approx.margin(static_cast<double>(newMargin));
13143 return *this;
13144 }
13145 template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
13146 ApproxMatcher& scale( T const& newScale ) {
13147 approx.scale(static_cast<double>(newScale));
13148 return *this;
13149 }
13150 };
13151
13152 template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
13153 class UnorderedEqualsMatcher final : public MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
13154 std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_target;
13155
13156 public:
13157 UnorderedEqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target):
13158 m_target(target)
13159 {}
13160 bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& vec) const override {
13161 if (m_target.size() != vec.size()) {
13162 return false;
13163 }
13164 return std::is_permutation(m_target.begin(), m_target.end(), vec.begin());
13165 }
13166
13167 std::string describe() const override {
13168 return "UnorderedEquals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify(m_target);
13169 }
13170 };
13171
13172
13173 // The following functions create the actual matcher objects.
13174 // This allows the types to be inferred
13175
13177 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
13178 ContainsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Contains( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
13179 return ContainsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
13180 }
13181
13183 template<typename T, typename Alloc = std::allocator<T>>
13184 VectorContainsElementMatcher<T, Alloc> VectorContains( T const& comparator ) {
13185 return VectorContainsElementMatcher<T, Alloc>(comparator);
13186 }
13187
13189 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
13190 EqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Equals( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
13191 return EqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
13192 }
13193
13195 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
13196 ApproxMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> Approx( std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator ) {
13197 return ApproxMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(comparator);
13198 }
13199
13201 template<typename T, typename AllocComp = std::allocator<T>, typename AllocMatch = AllocComp>
13202 UnorderedEqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch> UnorderedEquals(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target) {
13203 return UnorderedEqualsMatcher<T, AllocComp, AllocMatch>(target);
13204 }
13205
13206} // namespace Matchers
13207} // namespace Catch
13208
13209#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_VECTOR_HPP_INCLUDED
13210
13211#endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_ALL_HPP_INCLUDED

13327 void benchmarkPreparing( StringRef ) override {}

13331

13339 currentTestCaseInfo = &_testInfo;
13340 }

13344 }

13348

13351 }

13354 currentTestCaseInfo = nullptr;
13355 }
13356 void testRunEnded( TestRunStats const& /* _testRunStats */ ) override;
13357
13358 void skipTest(TestCaseInfo const&) override {
13359 // Don't do anything with this by default.
13360 // It can optionally be overridden in the derived class.
13361 }
13362
13363 protected:
13364 TestRunInfo currentTestRunInfo{ "test run has not started yet"_sr };
13365 TestCaseInfo const* currentTestCaseInfo = nullptr;
13366
13368 std::vector<SectionInfo> m_sectionStack;
13369 };

13527
13548 class CumulativeReporterBase : public ReporterBase {
13549 public:
13550 template<typename T, typename ChildNodeT>
13551 struct Node {
13552 explicit Node( T const& _value ) : value( _value ) {}
13553
13554 using ChildNodes = std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<ChildNodeT>>;
13555 T value;
13556 ChildNodes children;
13557 };
13558 struct SectionNode {
13559 explicit SectionNode(SectionStats const& _stats) : stats(_stats) {}
13560
13561 bool operator == (SectionNode const& other) const {
13562 return stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo == other.stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo;
13563 }
13564
13565 bool hasAnyAssertions() const;
13566
13567 SectionStats stats;
13568 std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<SectionNode>> childSections;
13569 std::vector<Detail::AssertionOrBenchmarkResult> assertionsAndBenchmarks;
13570 std::string stdOut;
13571 std::string stdErr;
13572 };
13573
13574
13575 using TestCaseNode = Node<TestCaseStats, SectionNode>;
13576 using TestRunNode = Node<TestRunStats, TestCaseNode>;
13577
13578 // GCC5 compat: we cannot use inherited constructor, because it
13579 // doesn't implement backport of P0136
13580 CumulativeReporterBase(ReporterConfig&& _config):
13581 ReporterBase(CATCH_MOVE(_config))
13582 {}
13583 ~CumulativeReporterBase() override;
13584
13585 void benchmarkPreparing( StringRef ) override {}
13586 void benchmarkStarting( BenchmarkInfo const& ) override {}
13587 void benchmarkEnded( BenchmarkStats<> const& benchmarkStats ) override;
13588 void benchmarkFailed( StringRef ) override {}
13589
13590 void noMatchingTestCases( StringRef ) override {}
13591 void reportInvalidTestSpec( StringRef ) override {}
13592 void fatalErrorEncountered( StringRef /*error*/ ) override {}
13593
13594 void testRunStarting( TestRunInfo const& ) override {}
13595
13596 void testCaseStarting( TestCaseInfo const& ) override {}
13597 void testCasePartialStarting( TestCaseInfo const&, uint64_t ) override {}
13598 void sectionStarting( SectionInfo const& sectionInfo ) override;
13599
13600 void assertionStarting( AssertionInfo const& ) override {}
13601
13602 void assertionEnded( AssertionStats const& assertionStats ) override;
13603 void sectionEnded( SectionStats const& sectionStats ) override;
13604 void testCasePartialEnded( TestCaseStats const&, uint64_t ) override {}
13605 void testCaseEnded( TestCaseStats const& testCaseStats ) override;
13606 void testRunEnded( TestRunStats const& testRunStats ) override;
13608 virtual void testRunEndedCumulative() = 0;
13609
13610 void skipTest(TestCaseInfo const&) override {}
13611
13612 protected:
13614 bool m_shouldStoreSuccesfulAssertions = true;
13616 bool m_shouldStoreFailedAssertions = true;
13617
13618 // We need lazy construction here. We should probably refactor it
13619 // later, after the events are redone.
13621 Detail::unique_ptr<TestRunNode> m_testRun;
13622
13623 private:
13624 // Note: We rely on pointer identity being stable, which is why
13625 // we store pointers to the nodes rather than the values.
13626 std::vector<Detail::unique_ptr<TestCaseNode>> m_testCases;
13627 // Root section of the _current_ test case
13628 Detail::unique_ptr<SectionNode> m_rootSection;
13629 // Deepest section of the _current_ test case
13630 SectionNode* m_deepestSection = nullptr;
13631 // Stack of _active_ sections in the _current_ test case
13632 std::vector<SectionNode*> m_sectionStack;
13633 };
13634
13635} // end namespace Catch

13995
13996 template <typename T, typename = void>
13997 struct has_description : std::false_type {};
13998
13999 template <typename T>
14000 struct has_description<
14001 T,
14002 void_t<decltype( T::getDescription() )>>
14003 : std::true_type {};
14004
14007 void registerReporterImpl( std::string const& name,
14008 IReporterFactoryPtr reporterPtr );
14010 void registerListenerImpl( Detail::unique_ptr<EventListenerFactory> listenerFactory );
14011 } // namespace Detail
14012
14013 class IEventListener;
14014 using IEventListenerPtr = Detail::unique_ptr<IEventListener>;
14015
14016 template <typename T>
14017 class ReporterFactory : public IReporterFactory {
14018
14019 IEventListenerPtr create( ReporterConfig&& config ) const override {
14020 return Detail::make_unique<T>( CATCH_MOVE(config) );
14021 }
14022
14023 std::string getDescription() const override {
14024 return T::getDescription();
14025 }
14026 };
14027
14028
14029 template<typename T>
14030 class ReporterRegistrar {
14031 public:
14032 explicit ReporterRegistrar( std::string const& name ) {
14033 registerReporterImpl( name,
14034 Detail::make_unique<ReporterFactory<T>>() );
14035 }
14036 };
14037
14038 template<typename T>
14039 class ListenerRegistrar {
14040
14041 class TypedListenerFactory : public EventListenerFactory {
14042 StringRef m_listenerName;
14043
14044 std::string getDescriptionImpl( std::true_type ) const {
14045 return T::getDescription();
14046 }
14047
14048 std::string getDescriptionImpl( std::false_type ) const {
14049 return "(No description provided)";
14050 }
14051
14052 public:
14053 TypedListenerFactory( StringRef listenerName ):
14054 m_listenerName( listenerName ) {}
14055
14056 IEventListenerPtr create( IConfig const* config ) const override {
14057 return Detail::make_unique<T>( config );
14058 }
14059
14060 StringRef getName() const override {
14061 return m_listenerName;
14062 }
14063
14064 std::string getDescription() const override {
14065 return getDescriptionImpl( Detail::has_description<T>{} );
14066 }
14067 };
14068
14069 public:
14070 ListenerRegistrar(StringRef listenerName) {
14071 registerListenerImpl( Detail::make_unique<TypedListenerFactory>(listenerName) );
14072 }
14073 };
14074}

14077
14078# define CATCH_REGISTER_REPORTER( name, reporterType ) \
14079 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
14080 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
14081 namespace { \
14082 const Catch::ReporterRegistrar<reporterType> \
14083 INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_RegistrarFor )( \
14084 name ); \
14085 } \
14086 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
14087
14088# define CATCH_REGISTER_LISTENER( listenerType ) \
14089 CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
14090 CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
14091 namespace { \
14092 const Catch::ListenerRegistrar<listenerType> \
14093 INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_RegistrarFor )( \
14094 #listenerType##_catch_sr ); \
14095 } \
14096 CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION
14097
14098#else // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE
14099
14100#define CATCH_REGISTER_REPORTER(name, reporterType)
14101#define CATCH_REGISTER_LISTENER(listenerType)
14102
14103#endif // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE
